(1460, 'default', 61, '<h1>\n	&nbsp;</h1>\n<h1>\n	&nbsp;</h1>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>\n	Local News &amp; Developments&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; ">The Sunnyvale City Council has voted 7-0 to ban foam food containers. &nbsp;The ordinance will make it illegal for retail food service vendors to distribute foam containers for food or liquid. To learn more and also find a list of vendors that supply alternatives to foam food containers visit&nbsp;</span><a href="http://sunnyvale.ca.gov/Departments/EnvironmentalServices/FoamFoodContainers.aspx" style="font-family: Arial; font-size: medium; ">http://sunnyvale.ca.gov/Departments/EnvironmentalServices/FoamFoodContainers.aspx</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>\n	Core Knowledge</h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Thinking about how you manage the materials you use on a daily basis is a big step towards developing sustainability within your organization. &nbsp;</span></p>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<h2>\n	Success Stories</h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Currently researching</span></p>\n<hr />\n<h2>\n	Tools &amp; Resources</h2>\n<h3 style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; ">\n	<span style="font-size:16px;"><u>Plastic Film Recycling</u></span></h3>\n<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; ">\n	<p style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="line-height: 15px; ">Does your company see a lot of plastic film? The plastic&nbsp;grocery&nbsp;bag is a commonly seen plastic film, but much of the plastic wrap in product packaging is the same material, PE or&nbsp;polyethylene, and there is a large market for it''s recovery. &nbsp;Visit&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.plasticbagrecycling.org/02.0/" style="line-height: 15px; ">http://www.plasticbagrecycling.org/02.0/</a><span style="line-height: 15px; ">&nbsp;for a calculator to determine the financial benefit of collecting this material, information on who will buy it and helpful strategies to ensure you get the most bang for your buck.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n	<h3>\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="line-height: 15px; "><u>Paper recycling and procurement</u></span></span></h3>\n	<p style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="line-height: 15px; ">The Environmental Paper Network (EPN) provides a&nbsp;compressive toolkit to guide your business to responsible paper usage. &nbsp;They provide&nbsp;tools&nbsp;for everything your company would need from start to finish including: model paper policies, an&nbsp;environmentally&nbsp;sound paper hierarchy, how to efficiently use your paper and even resources to help your suppliers verify the fiber content in their paper.&nbsp;Visit&nbsp;<u><font color="#0433FF"><a href="http://www.whatsinyourpaper.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=7&amp;Itemid=68">http://www.whatsinyourpaper.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=7&amp;Itemid=68</a></font></u>&nbsp;to get started. &nbsp;Also check out their applications for purchasers at&nbsp;</span><a href="http://environmentalpaper.org/purchaser-apps/" style="line-height: 15px; ">http://environmentalpaper.org/purchaser-apps/</a><span style="line-height: 15px; ">, which includes a&nbsp;calculator to measure and report the environmental benefits and savings with responsible paper procurement.</span></span></p>\n	<p style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="line-height: 15px; ">For making responsible paper purchases visit&nbsp;</span><a href="http://canopyplanet.org/EPD/" style="line-height: 15px; ">http://canopyplanet.org/EPD/</a><span style="line-height: 15px; ">&nbsp;for a great tool that ties in with the Paper Step (<u><font color="#0042aa"><a href="http://www.whatsinyourpaper.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=57&amp;Itemid=62">http://www.whatsinyourpaper.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=57&amp;Itemid=62</a></font></u>) from the Environmental Paper Network. &nbsp;You can search for paper based on types (printing, tissue,&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 15px; ">gift wrap, notepads, etc.) along&nbsp;with&nbsp;a variety of other fields like: ancient forest friendly, recycled content and brand name. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\n	<h3 style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><u>Finding value with your waste stream</u></span></h3>\n	<p style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; ">The By-Product Synergy (BPS) Network matches under-valued waste or by-product streams from one facility to potential users at another facility to create new revenues or savings with potential social and environmental benefits.&nbsp; This US Business Council for Sustainable Development (USBCSD) program takes it a step above a normal waste exchange by covering the technical, policy and </span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; ">financial</span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; "> </span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; ">hurdles</span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; ">&nbsp;to ensure the BPS effort is maximized.&nbsp; The diversity of businesses within their program also increases the possibilities by opening up synergies between industries that may have not otherwise become connected.&nbsp; In addition to materials they work to identify transportation, space, logistic and other resource synergies.&nbsp; To learn more and get involved </span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; ">visit </span><a href="http://bps-hub.org/" style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); " target="_blank">http://bps-hub.org/</a><span style="font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; ">.</span></span></p>\n	<h3 style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="line-height: 15px; "><u>Staying ahead of the game in waste reduction</u></span></span></h3>\n	<p style="position: static; z-index: auto; ">\n		<span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="line-height: 15px; ">The Northern California Recycling Association (NCRA) is a non-profit organization&nbsp;committed&nbsp;to promoting, expanding and&nbsp;institutionalizing&nbsp;recycling. &nbsp;This is a great group to get involved with to stay abreast in the recycling &amp; composting industry. &nbsp;They offer many classes, training, networking meetings and conferences. &nbsp;As stated on&nbsp;their site you are probably already benefiting from their work. &nbsp;If you are interested in staying ahead of the curve in managing your waste check out&nbsp;</span><a href="http://ncrarecycles.org/" style="line-height: 15px; ">http://ncrarecycles.org</a></span></p>\n</div>\n<h1>\n	&nbsp;</h1>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<a href="http://sunnyvale.ca.gov/Departments/EnvironmentalServices/FoamFoodContainers.aspx" style="font-family: Arial; font-size: medium; "><span id="cke_bm_101E" style="display: none; ">&nbsp;</span><span id="cke_bm_86E" style="display: none; ">&nbsp;</span></a></p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default'),
(1461, 'default', 115, '<p>\n	Biofuels are an energy source based on biological, or grown materials, for instance using corn to create <strong>ethanol</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	Biofuels have been an important source of energy in countries such as:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Spain</li>\n	<li>\n		Germany</li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, '');
Sustainable Activities</span></h2>\n<p>\n	The sustainability actions are either concerning the core services offered by eBay or its internal organization. Most of the internal organization actions are locally managed and assessed.</p>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Biodiversity/site</span></h3>\n<p>\n	<em>Local:</em></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Community gardens:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Organic community garden created by the Omaha (NE) Green Team: 70 employees gardeners worked 40 plots in 2010, and there is a waiting list to get a plot</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		Volunteering:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Salt Lake City team was recognized the most dedicated corporate group at <a href="http://www.treeutah.org/">Tree Utah</a> , having assisted with tree planting initiatives, restoration of wetlands annual fundraising efforts for several years</li>\n			<li>\n				Participation in Salt Lake City <a href="http://www.ebaygreenteam.com/posts/salt-lake-city-earth-day-fest">Earth Fest</a> and <a href="http://livegreenslc.wordpress.com/">Live Green Eco Fair</a></li>\n			<li>\n				47 employees from Swiss offices partnered with World Wildlife Fund to remove invasive plants and protect endangered species native to the <a href="http://www.valais.ch/en/welcome.cfm">Valaise region</a> of Switzerland</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Water</span></h3>\n<p>\n	No publicly available information.</p>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Energy</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Renewable energy in the USA:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Announced in Spring 2012 the Topaz data center in South Jordan, Utah, the first wholly owned data center, <a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/eBay-Goes-from-Green-to-Gold/4457">awarded LEED® Gold status by the US</a>GBC, creates power thanks to a solar array. It will produce 924,013 kilowatts hours (kWh) of clean electricity annually, &nbsp;which is equivalent to offsetting 702 tons of greenhouse gas emissions or planting 136 acres of pine forest. It is anticipated to pay for itself in 4 years</li>\n			<li>\n				Three solar arrays (665 kW in South Jordan, 650 kW in San Jose, 100 kW in Denver)and 500 kW Bloom Fuel cell installation in &nbsp;San Jose bring total renewable energy capacity to almost 2 Megawatts. That’s about 11% of eBay total US data center electricity demand. In 2013 eBay will open the first US data center that uses 100% renewable energy as primary power at their Utah site</li>\n			<li>\n				Less energy used to cool the data centers: minimum of 76% of energy going to computers in Arizona, and 95% in other states, against an industry average of 57%</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Energy efficient buildings in the USA and Germany:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Fall 2011: announced a new employee center in Draper (Utah) to be built and operated to LEED® Gold standards thanks to minimal construction waste, sustainable and locally-sourced building materials, high-efficiency heating and &nbsp;lighting, easy access to transit and green cleaning and landscaping practices. The facility will be opening in spring 2013.</li>\n			<li>\n				The site in Germany in 2010 was powered 100% with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydropower">hydropower electricity</a> and extended their renewable energy contract through 2012. When their new server room was constructed, they made sure to use the most efficient cooling system available and even increased the temperature to require less cooling system energy</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Lobbying:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Work with Republican State Senator Mark Madsen and others to <a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/eBays-Clean-Energy-Leadership-in-Utah/8420">pass Senate Bill 12</a>, a new piece of legislation that allows power-intensive utility customers like eBay to buy and transmit renewable power in Utah</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Materials</span></h3>\n<p>\n	<em>Global:</em></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		eBay reusable box pilot made from environmentally friendly materials: free reusable boxes provided to eBay sellers and buyers. Could protect nearly 4,000 trees, save 2.4 million gallons of water and conserve enough energy to power 49 homes for a year. This idea won the 2011 grand prize winning idea at the eBay Innovation Expo, as well as the eBay Green Team’s Big Green Idea contest. 100,000 boxes have been given away and 1,500 have been registered and reused. It resulted in the conservation of almost 7,000 gallons of water, an amount of energy sufficient to power 13 homes for a week, and reduced greenhouse gas emissions equivalent to taking 18 cars off the road for a week</li>\n	<li>\n		Partnership with USPS</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<em>Local:</em></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		USA: Omaha (Nebraska) Green Team:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				switch from plastic bottles to cans in the PayPal vending machines.</li>\n			<li>\n				the green team and the local Workplace Resource’s group partnered to provide employees with stainless steel flatware, ceramic coffee cups and reusable tumblers in break rooms and cafes</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		USA: StubHub Green Team in Connecticut:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				No more disposable cups</li>\n			<li>\n				Greening of local events and community outreach programs in partnership with the local CARE team</li>\n			<li>\n				Changed out their bathroom products for more environmentally friendly ones</li>\n			<li>\n				Enacted green education initiatives, and started a test group to rid the office of Post-It Notes entirely</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		USA: Headquarters in San Jose:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Workplace resource’s group launched in 2010 the <a href="http://www.ebaygreenteam.com/posts/trash-cans-for-compost-bins-san-jose">Zero Waste for Green Space</a> program, aiming at zero waste going to the Landfill. Most trashcans were replaced with recycling and compost cans and the San Jose campuses now have a diversion rate over 95% (program in partnership with Republic Services)</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Israel:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Biodegradable kitchenware</li>\n			<li>\n				Double-sided printers</li>\n			<li>\n				Bike sharing program</li>\n			<li>\n				Drastic reduction of trash going to landfills&nbsp;</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		eBay Canada:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				All branded goods are either made of recycled materials, can be recycled, or are reusable. Their office pens are made of 65% organic materials directly from renewable energy developers</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Transportation/Air Quality</span></h3>\n<p>\n	<em>Local:</em></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Omaha employees biked over 9,880 miles last year and were certified a Bronze level <a href="http://www.bikeleague.org/programs/bicyclefriendlyamerica/bicyclefriendlybusiness/bfb_paypal.php">Bike Friendly Business</a> by the <a href="http://www.bikeleague.org/index.php">League of American Bicyclists</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Preferred parking program for environmentally friendly cars in Salt Lake City</li>\n	<li>\n		In Israel, subsidized leasing program for Hybrid cars and bike racks</li>\n	<li>\n		In Switzerland: bikes available to commute to train stations, coordination of lunch&nbsp;deliveries with existing local schedules to minimize driving of providers. Alternative commute program</li>\n	<li>\n		In Bern (Switzerland) used by 70% of employees</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<em>Global:</em></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Website giving greener driving tips and services: <a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/Introducing-eBay-Green-Driving/8536">http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/Introducing-eBay-Green-Driving/8536</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Partnerships:</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Shows and events in San Jose (e-waste sale, electric car showcase, etc.)</li>\n	<li>\n		Work with Net Impact to help them advance an entrepreneurial sustainability culture</li>\n	<li>\n		Writing of “Making Your Impact at Work” guide in 2009</li>\n	<li>\n		Organization of creative reuse competition</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Sustainability-related services:</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Largest marketplace for used, refurbished and vintage goods</li>\n	<li>\n		Created two specialized websites to buy/sell sustainable products (socially and environmentally respectful):\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				green.ebay.com since 2009: inviting users to join the “Green Team” (300,000 members today)</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		Maintain a blog giving green tips to users on what to buy, how to use products and what to do to be greener</li>\n	<li>\n		Offer a specialized platform to sell pre-owned electronics <a href="http://instantsale.ebay.com/">ebay instant sale</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Sustainability Governance</span></h2>\n<p>\n	The sustainability program at eBay started with 40 employees at the San Jose site in 2007, when they formed the first Green Team. Today, employees forming the Green Team is made of 2,500+ employees in 25 countries. eBay’s sustainability program uses a bottom-up process: each site is coming up with ideas and actions it implements. All members of the extensive Green Team also collaborate on a few global projects.</p>\n<p>\n	<u>eBay contributors to the Green ebay website</u></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Annie Lescroart Senior Manager, Sustainability Communications</li>\n	<li>\n		Caitlin Bristol Manager, eBay Green + Sustainability</li>\n	<li>\n		Danielle Huffaker Merchandising Manager</li>\n	<li>\n		Dean Nelson Senior Director, Global Foundation Services</li>\n	<li>\n		Gaurav Rekhi Product Manager, Social Innovation</li>\n	<li>\n		Jill Primost Sustainable Commerce</li>\n	<li>\n		Kevin Wolfley eBay Green Canada</li>\n	<li>\n		Lori Duvall Director of Operational Sustainability</li>\n	<li>\n		Lorin May Head of EU Charity &amp; Sustainability</li>\n	<li>\n		Pat Kohl Facility Operations Manager</li>\n	<li>\n		Siddharth Sanghvi GM, Sustainable Commerce</li>\n	<li>\n		JD Norton Community Manager</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<u>Guest contributors to the Green ebay website</u></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Brad Berman Hybrid &amp; Electric Vehicle Expert</li>\n	<li>\n		Danna Crawford eBay Seller</li>\n	<li>\n		Gabrielle Maguire 2011 Climate Corps Fellow</li>\n	<li>\n		Sheena Matheiken Founder, The Uniform Project</li>\n	<li>\n		The Inside Source eBay''s Digital Media Destination</li>\n	<li>\n		Zem Joaquin eBay Eco Lifestyle Expert</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Challenges and Future Goals </span></h2>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Use frameworks to make the sustainability policy more consistent at the corporate scale and to compare actions to an objective scale&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		Establish a system to measure results of sustainability actions in terms of savings (resource, energy, CO2, money)</li>\n	<li>\n		Publish a Sustainability Report</li>\n	<li>\n		Partner with assessment firms and programs</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Best practices, Success Drivers</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<em>Internal actions</em>:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Aggressive data center efficiency program yielding &gt; 50% improvement in transaction efficiency since 2008</li>\n	<li>\n		Involved a large number of people from diverse offices around the globe, rewarding&nbsp;them for their local collective efforts</li>\n	<li>\n		Took advantage of the creativity of each one in the firm. Reduced costs and expanded impact of the sustainability effort by engaging regular eBay employees and internet users and visitors into green teams (more than 300,000 members in the&nbsp;online community)</li>\n	<li>\n		Adapted each office sustainability policy to its situation, opportunities and needs</li>\n	<li>\n		Communicated through a Blog on the green teams’ actions, using a platform and&nbsp;tone less formal and likely to appeal to eBay users, getting them to join the global green team</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<em>Core business/services</em>:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		“Belief that people are good and when offered the tools, resources and knowledge, they shop in ways that are better for the planet”, stated on ebay website&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		More than 100 billion worth of reused products have been sold on eBay since 1998</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: center; ">\n	<em>Researched and prepared by Caroline Nowacki for Sustainable Silicon Valley</em></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Sources:</span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/ebay/blog/Engaging-People/25">http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/ebay/blog/Engaging-People/25</a></li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/eBay-Green-Team-2010-Year-in-Review/4467">http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/eBay-Green-Team-2010-Year-in-Review/4467</a></li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/about/">http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/about/</a></li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/eBay-and-Dell-Recognized-for-Data-Center-Efficiency-Leadership/8527">http://green.ebay.com/greenteam/blog/eBay-and-Dell-Recognized-for-Data-Center-Efficiency-Leadership/8527</a></li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://specials.kenan-flagler.unc.edu/kicse/ORIG%20Shared%20Documents/Measuring%20Sustainability.pdf">http://specials.kenan-flagler.unc.edu/kicse/ORIG%20Shared%20Documents/Measuring%20Sustainability.pdf</a></li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="https://www.cdproject.net/CDPResults/CDP-G500-2011-Report.pdf">https://www.cdproject.net/CDPResults/CDP-G500-2011-Report.pdf</a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, ''),
