		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		Global Reporting Initiative:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://www.ibm.com/ibm/responsibility/gri.shtml">http://www.ibm.com/ibm/responsibility/gri.shtml</a></li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		Voluntary Environmental Initiatives:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://www.ibm.com/ibm/environment/initiatives/">http://www.ibm.com/ibm/environment/initiatives/</a></li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		Materials potentially harmful for health:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				<u>http://www.ibm.com/ibm/environment/annual/IBMEnvReport_2011.pdf)</u></li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, ''),
(1510, 'default', 109, '<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	Sustainable Silicon Valley just completed a review of the sustainability practices of 15 leading companies in sustainability. Here are the three Sustainability Trends SSV observed:</p>\n<p style="margin-left: 75.35pt; text-align: justify; ">\n	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Multiplication of sustainable transportation initiatives</p>\n<p style="margin-left: 75.35pt; text-align: justify; ">\n	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New reusable and fully recyclable packaging</p>\n<p style="margin-left: 1.05in; text-align: justify; ">\n	3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cradle-to-cradle product design</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	<strong><u>Reducing the CO2 emissions of employees’ commutes</u></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	The Google buses are among the most well known companies’ transportation initiatives, but apart from it being a multi-occupancy vehicle, did you know that their shuttle used biodiesel and transported over 4,500 employees everyday?&nbsp; In addition to this Shuttle program, Google has created GFleet: a car-sharing program composed of energy-efficient vehicles including electric plug-ins. These two initiatives have resulted in a net annual saving of more than 5400 metric tons of CO2.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	Microsoft has also created one of the world’s largest private bus systems, called the “Connector”, for its Seattle’s campus, WA, and their drivers follow a 5-minute “low or no idle” rule to help reduce emissions. But apart from these private solutions, partnering with other public or private systems is a good alternative. Microsoft also subsidizes regional public transportation. HP enables employees to take advantage of WageWorks and use pretax income to pay for public transport costs. HP also encourages carpooling options, notably through a partnership with rideshare.org in the San Francisco Bay Area.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	<strong><u>Reusable and fully recyclable packaging</u></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	Sustainable Packaging is also a hot topic in which companies such as eBay, Coca-Cola, SAP, and HP are innovating.&nbsp; For example, eBay crowd-sourced through a contest, a solution of reusable boxes made from environmentally friendly materials. Making it available to its buyers and sellers has resulted in the conservation of almost 7,000 gallons of water, an amount of energy sufficient to power 13 homes for a week, and a reduced greenhouse gas emissions amount equivalent to taking 18 cars off the road.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	Coca-Cola’s PlantBottle program is another example and the first ever fully recyclable PET bottle made partially from plant-based materials. It led to a reduction of approximately one-third of the petroleum-based material that was traditionally used to make PET bottles.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	<strong><u>Cradle-to-Cradle product design</u></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	A final trend observed in companies such as HP, Cisco or Patagonia, is the effort to help customers efficiently recycle their old products.&nbsp; HP’s worldwide ink cartridge recycling Planet Partner program provides customers with an easy and free way to recycle their old cartridges.&nbsp; HP recycles the old cartridges and collects PET plastic to create new HP Original Ink Cartridges.&nbsp; This program reduced HP’s Carbon Footprint by 33%, decreased their water use by up to 89%, and lowered their fossil fuel depletion by 62%.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	Patagonia’s worldwide recycling initiative, called the Common Threads Recycling Program, actually asks its customers not to buy what they do not need! It offers customers to repair their Patagonia gear, find a home for gear no longer needed and buy it back from customers, and finally recycle worn out gear into new fiber and fabric.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	<em>The complete reviews of the 15 companies will be on EcoCloud by the end of January 2013, don’t forget to check it out!</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify; ">\n	<u>More information on companies'' websites</u>:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		Google Commute:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.google.com/green/efficiency/oncampus/#commuting">http://www.google.com/green/efficiency/oncampus/#commuting</a></li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		Ebay reusable box:&nbsp;<a href="http://thebox.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?EbayGreenBox">http://thebox.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?EbayGreenBox</a></li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		Microsoft:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/news/misc/09-06connectorFS.aspx">http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/news/misc/09-06connectorFS.aspx</a></li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		Coca-Cola Plant Bottle Program:</li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		<a href="http://www.thecoca-colacompany.com/citizenship/plantbottle.html">http://www.thecoca-colacompany.com/citizenship/plantbottle.html</a></li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		Patagonia:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.patagonia.com/us/common-threads/">http://www.patagonia.com/us/common-threads/</a></li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		HP Cartridge Recycling Program:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.hp.com/sbso/product/supplies/cartridge-recycling.html">http://www.hp.com/sbso/product/supplies/cartridge-recycling.html</a></li>\n	<li style="text-align: justify; ">\n		SAP:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sapsustainabilityreport.com/materials-used">http://www.sapsustainabilityreport.com/materials-used</a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, ''),
(1518, 'default', 131, '<img alt="wrappingpaper.jpg" class="pyro-image alignment-left" src="{{ url:site }}files/thumb/67/0" style="float: left; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; " />\n\n<p>\n	<strong>Thinking and Acting with Sustainability in Mind During the Holidays</strong></p>\n<p>\n	In late December every year, waste generation goes up at least 25%. &nbsp;Consider resisting the siren call of advertising and cultural pressure and challenge yourself to make different choices as you go along the holiday season.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Some basic goals for the holidays:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Vote with your dollars:</strong>&nbsp;Think outside the big box store and look for something local, fair trade, sustainably produced. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.calrecycle.ca.gov/RecycleStore/" target="_blank">CalRecyle</a>&nbsp;has some great items made with recycled content to get you thinking.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Wrap it with re-use:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Use fabric, use decorative bags, use interesting boxes by <a href="http://www.onearth.org/blog/wrap-responsibly">Wrapping Responsibly</a>. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.recycleworks.org/resident/giftsandpackaging.html#gifts" target="_blank">RecycleWorks</a>&nbsp;has many great ideas for gifts and wrapping as well.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Wrap it with recycling:</strong>&nbsp;That metallic wrapping paper sure is pretty, but it can''t be recycled. &nbsp;Let go of the glam when buying wrapping paper, and if you feel like it, try getting the paper off of gifts you receive somewhat intact so you can use it again. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>More inspiration for less-is-more holidays:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Make enjoying and honoring the world around you part of your holidays:&nbsp;<a href="http://wilderness.org/content/green-holiday-ideas-make-your-holidays-easy-earth" target="_blank">The Wilderness Society</a>&nbsp;has brought together many great ideas for gift giving, decorating and even eating during the holidays.</p>\n<p>\n	As the&nbsp;<a href="http://sierraclub.typepad.com/" target="_blank">Sierra Club</a>&nbsp;says, ''tis the season for consumption, and they have many ideas to help rein it all in, including a good one that is easy to forget--bring your own bag to every store, not just the grocery store.</p>\n<p>\n	Feeling economically constrained but still want to embrace your eco values? &nbsp;Here are some&nbsp;<a href="http://sierraclub.typepad.com/greenlife/2011/11/going-green-on-a-tight-budget-deals-and-bargains.html" target="_blank">budget friendly tips</a>&nbsp;for that, too.</p>\n<p>\n	If you are ready to think completely outside the box, there are many gifts that support worthy causes, such as the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nrdcgreengifts.org/" target="_blank">Natural Resources Defense Council</a>, which offers gift-versions of support for various causes.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<div>\n	<strong>For a super sustainable holiday gift idea</strong>, how about&nbsp;<a href="https://www.sustainablesv.org/civicrm/contribute/transact?reset=1&amp;id=1" target="_self">giving Sustainable Silicon Valley a donation</a>? We have a wish list if you want ideas or have something you could re-gift to us. Tax-deductible, too!</div>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, ''),
(1519, 'default', 130, '<img alt="earthday2012page.jpg" class="pyro-image alignment-right" src="{{ url:site }}files/thumb/68/0" style="float: right; margin: 10px; " />\n\n<div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">\n	<p>\n		<strong>Earth Day Ideas to Challenge and Inspire: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\n	<p>\n		<b>Idea #1 Audit and Act:&nbsp; Understand and Reduce Your Energy and Water Use</b></p>\n	<p>\n		Energy Use:&nbsp;National Geographic invites you to The&nbsp;<a href="http://environment.nationalgeographic.com/environment/energy/great-energy-challenge/">Great Energy Challenge</a>&nbsp;which is a National Geographic initiative to help you understand our current energy situation. Explore the GEC to figure out and trim your carbon footprint using the&nbsp;<a href="http://environment.nationalgeographic.com/environment/energy/great-energy-challenge/personal-energy-meter/">Personal Energy Meter Tool</a>. Share your scores and challenge friends!</p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Water Use:&nbsp;</span>Free audits and water-saving device giveaways are available to customers through San Jose Water’s&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sjwater.com/for_your_information/save_water_money/water_audit_program/">Water Audit Program</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;Santa Clara Valley Water District’s&nbsp;<a href="http://www.save20gallons.org/">Save20Gallons</a>&nbsp;challenge. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n	<p>\n		<b>Idea #2 Tap Water Campaign</b></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Challenge yourself and others to give up using bottled water:&nbsp; Fun facts and solutions are available from The Story of Stuff creator Annie Leonard:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.storyofstuff.org/movies-all/story-of-bottled-water/">The Story of Bottled Water</a></span><br />\n		<br />\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #3 Reduce Trash</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Who’s the sparest of them all?&nbsp; Maybe some employees or departments will want to start a friendly competition! &nbsp;Need some inspiration?&nbsp; It’s time to rethink everything.&nbsp; Check out the&nbsp;<a href="http://zerowastehome.blogspot.com/p/tips.html">Zero Waste Family</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;or follow the journey of Beth Terry of Oakland, CA who gave up using plastic in 2007 and has been blogging about it ever since, first as “fake plastic fish” and now as&nbsp;<a href="http://myplasticfreelife.com/">My Plastic-Free Life</a>. &nbsp;Another resource and idea is to dive into trying out a zero-waste lifestyle issued by&nbsp;<a href="http://noimpactproject.org/">No Impact Man</a>.</span><br />\n		<br />\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #4 Take Small Actions</b><br />\n		Everyone can do at least one little thing, right?<b>&nbsp;</b>&nbsp;And just imagine if everyone did!&nbsp; Any group of individuals can create a group on the website&nbsp;<a href="http://www.onemillionactsofgreen.com/">One Million Acts of Green</a>&nbsp;and start a competition.&nbsp; There are lists of “Green Acts” to choose from in various categories. &nbsp;Another idea is to take a DOT (<a href="http://acespace.org/dot">Do One Thing</a>) pledge, maybe consider joining a team, and rack up the DOTs and compare!</span><br />\n		<br />\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #5 Eco-Friendly&nbsp;Garden</b><br />\n		Challenge employees to start a garden, or even a planter on a balcony!</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Garden or Backyard Habitat&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.nwf.org/How-to-Help/Garden-for-Wildlife.aspx">http://www.nwf.org/How-to-Help/Garden-for-Wildlife.aspx</a><br />\n		<span class="font-size-2">California&nbsp;Native Plants:&nbsp;<a href="http://cnps.org/">http://cnps.org/</a></span><br />\n		<span class="font-size-2">Bay Area&nbsp;Friendly Landscaping:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bayfriendlycoalition.org/">http://www.bayfriendlycoalition.org/&nbsp;</a></span><br />\n		<br />\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #7 Buy Less Pledge</b><br />\n		We all have too much stuff.&nbsp; How about making an Earth Day compact among employees to&nbsp;<a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/thecompact/">Buy Nothing New for a Year</a>&nbsp;(or month).</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Okay, so no new stuff, but what about all the old stuff?&nbsp; Give away your unwanted stuff or get what you want, for free:&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.freecycle.org/" target="_blank">www.freecycle.org</a>&nbsp; or exchange at:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.swapstyle.com/" target="_blank">www.swapstyle.com/</a></span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #8&nbsp; Buy Responsibly</b></span><br />\n		<span class="font-size-2">Challenge yourself to buy local, fair-trade, and organic.&nbsp; Follow your conscience to the mall . . . or the website!&nbsp; Eco-friendly shopping options abound now, but to give you some ideas, check out:&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.greenhome.com/" target="_blank">www.greenhome.com</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.biggreenpurse.com/" target="_blank">www.biggreenpurse.com</a>, and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.greenerprinter.com/grp/welcome.do">http://www.greenerprinter.com/grp/welcome.do</a></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">and, for a massive infusion of green-available-everything ideas, go to a&nbsp;<a href="http://www.greenfestivals.org/">Green Fest</a>&nbsp;near you.</span><br />\n		<br />\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #9 Eco-Friendly Eating</b><br />\n		Eat local, eat less meat, eat no meat, eat all organic—design a challenge to pull people out of their normal habits and into some that will benefit their bodies and the planet.&nbsp;</span></p>\n	<p>\n		Support&nbsp;<a href="http://www.foodroutes.org/">Local Farms</a>&nbsp;or find a&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cafarmersmarkets.com/index.cfm">Farmers Market</a>&nbsp;near you (California only).</p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Try eating less meat and learn about the health benefits of a vegetarian diet by&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.pcrm.org/health/veginfo/index.html">Physicians Committee</a>.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.meatlessmonday.com/spread-the-movement/">Meatless Monday</a>&nbsp;is an initiative that aims to reduce meat consumption by 15% in order to improve personal health and the health of the planet. Maybe it can be implemented at the company cafeteria?</p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Package your food responsibly too!&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://lifewithoutplastic.com/">http://lifewithoutplastic.com/</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.laptoplunches.com/">http://www.laptoplunches.com/</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.lunchsense.com/">http://www.lunchsense.com/</a>&nbsp;give some fun new ideas, but you can also just dig out some of the re-usable plastic or glass containers you already have and load them up!&nbsp; Look into getting your company logo on some quality re-usable containers as prizes for employees who bring lunch for a whole week, or go meatless.</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<b>Idea # 10 Reduce Car Trips</b></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Start a carpool or grease that bike and get ready to use less of your car. Here are some resources to encourage you and colleagues to reducing car trips:</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.511.org/">511.org</a>&nbsp;can help you plan your trip using public transportation in the Bay Area</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.youcanbikethere.com/">Bike to Work</a></span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://2milechallenge.com/">Clif Bar 2 Mile Challenge</a>:&nbsp; Pick a bike-promoting charity and see if your team wins!</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.vanpool.com/">Vanpools</a>:&nbsp; Organize a vanpool and let someone else do the driving</span></p>\n	<p>\n		<b>Idea #11 Green Business Certification</b></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Make it official:&nbsp; Get a green business certification for your company:&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/" target="_blank">http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gbb.org/" target="_blank">http://www.gbb.org/</a></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Green Business Certification for small businesses:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sba.gov/content/green-certification-and-ecolabeling" target="_blank">http://www.sba.gov/content/green-certification-and-ecolabeling</a></span></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Sustainability in Multi-Tenant Spaces and other facilities:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.thegbi.org/green-globes/" target="_blank">http://www.thegbi.org/green-globes/</a></span></p>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, ''),
