(1330, 'default', 38, '<p>\n	By <author class="name">Anuradha Munshi</author><author class="title">, EcoCloud Energy Lead</author></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="current" style="text-align: left;">\n	Energy efficiency can be improved by using less energy to accomplish a particular task. For example, insulating a home allows a building to use less energy to maintain a desired temperature. Another example is that compact fluorescent lights use two-thirds less energy and may last 6 to 10 times longer than incandescent lights.</p>\n<p>\n	Improvements in energy efficiency are most often achieved by incorporating a more efficient technology or production process.</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt="cleanvehicletech" class="pyro-image alignment-none" src="{{ url:site }}files/thumb/47/0" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>\n	<span style="color: rgb(0, 51, 102);"><strong><span class="font-size-3">Most Energy Used in Commercial Buildings goes to Space heating</span></strong></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<img alt="EnergyUsageinUSA" class="pyro-image alignment-none" height="421" src="{{ url:site }}files/thumb/48/0" width="505" /></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-1">Source: U.S. Energy Information Administration</span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default'),
