(1443, 'default', 114, '<p style="text-align: center; ">\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img alt="SAP" class="pyro-image alignment-none" src="{{ url:site }}files/large/90" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center; ">\n	<strong style="font-size: 18px; ">SAP Sustainability Review</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center; ">\n	<strong style="font-size: 16px; ">January 2013</strong></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Introduction</span></h2>\n<p>\n	SAP is a German software corporation that innovates business management software, applications and services. They started an organized and broad sustainability effort in 2009. Their sustainability efforts are detailed in comprehensive online sustainability reports including GRI and UN Global Compact indexes. In addition, SAP partners with organizations such as the Sustainability Consortium, Carbon Disclosure Project, and Business for Social Responsibility.</p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Awards, frameworks and accomplishments as of Nov. 2012</span></h2>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Sustainability Awards</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		2012 Technology Innovation Award by Ventana Research for SAP’s innovative approach and market introduction of SAP for Automotive Cloud and SAP for Utilities Cloud. (<a href="http://www.sap.com/news-reader/index.epx?pressid=19535">http://www.sap.com/news-reader/index.epx?pressid=19535</a>)</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		SAP’s Palo Alto building was awarded by the City of Palo Alto with the Green Business Leader Award for achieving major strides in improving building energy efficiency</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		BCA Greenmark Award 2012 Gold for SAP’s office building in Singapore</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		Two 2012 Social Innovation Awards in recognition of SAP’s Sustainability Report presented by JustMeans</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		<a href="http://www.prnewsonline.com/CSRawards2012/">PR&nbsp;News'' 2012 CSR Awards</a></li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		SAP’s Shea-Butter video <a href="http://www.sap-tv.com/video/7334">http://www.sap-tv.com/video/7334</a> has won the intermedia-globe GOLD Award in the category Public Relations: Human Relations and Values</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		SAP was recognized as a leader in a <a href="http://www.sustainabilityleadershipreport.com/">Sustainability Leadership Report</a> by <a href="http://www.brandlogic.com/">BrandLogic</a>, which measures real performance vs. perceived sustainability progress, showing the importance of &nbsp;sustainability communications</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Listings/Index</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		FTSE4Good (since 2007) - Link</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Dow Jones Sustainability Index (SAP leads the software industry for the sixth consecutive year) <a href="http://www.sustainability-index.com/">- Link </a></li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Global Challenges Index (among the first 100 firms selected when the index was founded in 2007) - Link</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Global 100 (Corporate Knights Inc. and Innovest Strategic Value Advisors ranking) - Link NASDAQ OMX CRD Global Sustainability 50 Index - Link&nbsp;</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Oekom Prime Rating - Link</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Inclusion in the Greenpeace Cool IT Leaderboard - Link</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Inclusion in the Ethibel PIONEER and Ethibel EXCELLENCE Investment Registers - Link</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		STOXX® Global ESG Leaders - Link</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Rankings</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		&nbsp;# 8 in 2012 global Newsweek''s "Green Rankings" (<a href="http://www.thedailybeast.com/newsweek/2011/10/16/green-rankings-2011-america-s-greenest-companies-photos.all.html">Link2012</a>) -<a href="http://www.thedailybeast.com/newsweek/2011/10/17/green-rankings-2011-30-greenest-tech-companies-from-google-to-ibm.html"> #20 in 2011 global rankings (Link2011)</a></li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Among top 50 of Interbrand''s "Best Global Green Brands 2012" ranking - Link</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Inclusion in the Greenpeace Cool IT Leaderboard - <a href="http://www.greenpeace.org/international/en/campaigns/climate-change/cool-it/leaderboard/SAP/">Link</a></li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		SAP Canada has been selected as one of <a href="https://blogs.wdf.sap.corp/NorthAmericaNews/2012/10/18/sap-canada-top-50-employers/best_employer_canada/">Canada’s 50 Best Employers for 2013</a></li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		The U.S Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) recognized SAP America as one of the <a href="http://www.epa.gov/greenpower/toplists/top20tech.htm">Top 20 Tech and Telecom green power users</a> for its purchase of electricity generated from renewable sources</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Frameworks</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Sustainability reports according to GRI guidelines and published on Internet since 2008 (Level C in 2008, accredited by KPMG since 2009, level A+ since 2010 report)</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.5pt; ">\n		Measured its scope 3 emissions (upstream and downstream emissions included) for the first time in 2011, working with the WRI to develop a new standard</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 31.7pt; ">\n		UN Global Compact member since 2000. “Communications On Progress” conform to the three requirements of UN Global Compact and published in 2005, and then each year from 2007 to today</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Sustainable Activities</span></h2>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Biodiversity/Site</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Biodiversity protection with green roofs, ground sealing, rainwater infiltration, planting hayfields, and sustainable landscaping</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Water</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Run-off water for irrigation and toilets in Germany</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Waterless washroom fixtures, installed pressure reduction valves and reduced flush toilets in offices in Brazil, Canada, India, Israel, Singapore, Switzerland, and the United States</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Energy</span></h3>\n<p>\n	Total energy increase from 845 GWh in 2010 to 860 GWh in 2011, but:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		+ 23 electric cars in the corporate car fleet =&gt; increase of fuel consumption non proportionate to the increase in the number of cars</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		7% decrease in office electricity usage in 2011 compared to 2010: improved lighting, cooling and heating systems; “smart buildings” tracking the use of electricity and managing it</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		LEED gold and platinum certifications in some countries, ISO 14001 standards in others</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Investment in renewable energies: 47% of total electricity usage in 2011, compared to 45% in 2010 an 16% in 2009</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		50% of headquarters’ energy is from renewable sources thanks to electricity bought from a local hydro production.</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Increase from 52% to 65% of server virtualization of entire IT landscape. Desktop virtualization has helped reduce the number of PCs per employee</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Facility management software improving energy and carbon management in 350 facilities worldwide: energy usage breakdown and comparison of facilities efficiency around the world</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Optimization of system configurations to lower power usage within data centers</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Avoided costs of a quarter billion US dollars since 2008 related to Greenhouse Gas emissions reductions</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Materials</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Reduction of packaging for products: Blu-Ray discs for greater data storage, downloading of software and handbooks instead of hard copies</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Reduction of number of pages printed per employee thanks to: double-sided printing, scanning instead of copying (e.g. for expense reports), reducing number of printers, increasing employee awareness using a printing tracker on the SAP software</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Results were 2% reduction in pages printed (goal was 5% for 2011)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Transportation</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Use of Cisco services for teleconferences to reduce the number of business trips</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Partnerships around sustainability (engaging suppliers)</span></h3>\n<p>\n	80% comes from downstream emissions (use of products) so 3-step policy focusing on product use:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Work with hardware providers to help increase hardware efficiency</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Benchmark of hardware provider products available to customers to optimize the energy efficiency of their servers</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		High-efficiency data center management knowledge, experienced and shared with clients</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Sustainability-related products and services</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Energy-efficient software thanks to streamlined databases and in-memory solutions: up to 60% electricity saved with SAP NetWeaver® Process Integration technology</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Work with CDP to include energy and carbon management applications:\n		<ul>\n			<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n				Sustainability map for EcoHub solution marketplace of green IT solutions and services.</li>\n			<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n				CDP Reporter Services, supporting an organization’s carbon management and disclosure process and includes a range of programs such as Investor CDP, CDP Supply Chain and CDP Water Disclosure.</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Simpler software design, running on fewer servers to require less energy</li>\n	<li style="margin-left: 0.5in; ">\n		Software solutions that help SAP customers create more sustainable businesses and address the following challenges: energy management, sustainable supply chain, operational risk management, sustainable workforce, and sustainability reporting and analytics.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Challenges and Future Goals INSERT INTO `page_chunks` (`id`, `slug`, `page_id`, `body`, `parsed`, `type`, `sort`, `class`) VALUES
(1462, 'default', 65, '<p class="bread_crumb">\n	<strong>Design for the Environment Program</strong> is a United States Environmental Protection Agency (USEPA) program, created in 1992, that works to prevent pollution, and the risk pollution presents to humans and the environment.</p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">The EPA DfE program provides information regarding safer electronics, safer flame retardants, safer chemical formulations, as well as best environmental practices.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">DfE employs a variety of design approaches that attempt to reduce the overall human health and environmental impact of a product, process or service, where impacts are considered across its life cycle. Different software tools have been developed to assist designers in finding optimized products (or processes/services).</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">&nbsp;The three main goals of DfE are:</span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Promoting green cleaning and recognizing safer consumer and industrial and institutional products through safer product labeling.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Defining Best Practices in areas ranging from auto refinishing to nail salon safety.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2">Identifying safer chemicals, including life cycle considerations, through Alternatives Assessment.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">&nbsp;</span><span class="font-size-2">Source: wikipedia</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://api.ning.com:80/files/JhiStCwBHQKUR19M*Te2C7iZC3yjRC0RbYlWV1p9hUMSiMd4rt4SIgoyVQ2Uf7cl9U3eOSFxg5AF6l9W*OkH5GXJmaJiuHJ6/DesignforEnv_logo.jpg" target="_self"><img class="align-left" src="http://api.ning.com:80/files/JhiStCwBHQKUR19M*Te2C7iZC3yjRC0RbYlWV1p9hUMSiMd4rt4SIgoyVQ2Uf7cl9U3eOSFxg5AF6l9W*OkH5GXJmaJiuHJ6/DesignforEnv_logo.jpg" width="160" /></a></span><span class="font-size-2"><strong><span style="color: #008080;">The Design for the Environment Safer Product</span></strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><strong><span style="color: #008080;">Labeling Program</span></strong> advances EPA''s mission to protect human health and the environment. The program uses EPA''s chemical expertise and resources to carefully evaluate products and to label only those that have met the program''s highly protective standards. By allowing use of the logo on products, EPA empowers consumers and commercial purchasers to select safer chemical products that do not sacrifice quality or performance—and are safer for people and the planet. Design for the Environment labels a variety of chemical-based products, like all-purpose cleaners, laundry detergents, and carpet and floor care products. Look for the Design for the Environment logo when you shop or procure products and join this national effort to protect human and environmental health.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Product manufacturers who become Design for the Environment partners and earn the right to display the Design for the Environment logo on recognized products have invested heavily in research, development and reformulation, to ensure that their ingredients and finished product line up on the green end of the health and environmental spectrum, while maintaining or improving product performance.&nbsp;The Design for the Environment label is recognized by retailers as a mark of environmental superiority. To consumers, the mark means that products are better for health and the environment.</span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.epa.gov/dfe/pubs/projects/formulat/about.htm">How to Partner, Get the DfE Label</a></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.epa.gov/dfe/standard_for_safer_cleaning_products.pdf">DfE Standard for Safer Cleaning Products (PDF)</a>&nbsp;(31 pp., 177 K,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.epa.gov/epahome/pdf.html">about PDF</a>)</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.epa.gov/dfe/pubs/formulat/draft_boilerplate_partnership_agreement%20_cleaning_products_website.pdf">Partnership Agreement (PDF)</a>&nbsp;(10 pp., 44 K,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.epa.gov/epahome/pdf.html">about PDF</a>)</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.epa.gov/dfe/pubs/projects/gfcp/index.htm">DfE Criteria for Safer Chemical Ingredients</a></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.cleangredients.org/">CleanGredients®</a>&nbsp;(database of safer ingredients)&nbsp;<a href="http://www.epa.gov/epahome/exitepa.htm"><img alt="Link to EPA''s External Link Disclaimer" height="13" src="http://www.epa.gov/epafiles/images/epafiles_misc_exitepadisc.gif" width="87" /></a></span></li>\n</ul>\n<div id="page_note">\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-2"><b>&nbsp;</b></span></p>\n	<p>\n		&nbsp;</p>\n	<p>\n		&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default'),
(1466, 'default', 68, '<div class="bread_crumb">\n	<strong style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0); "><span class="font-size-4">Mandatory Commercial Recycling Law</span></strong></div>\n<div class="bread_crumb">\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div id="xf_navigation">\n	<p class="Default">\n		In an effort to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, the state of California has passed legislation to create a statewide program to <span style="color: #003300;"><b>divert 75% of commercial solid waste from landfills by 2020 (AB 341).</b></span> AB 341 plans to achieve this by requiring all businesses that generate 4 cubic yards or more of commercial solid waste per week, and multifamily residences with 5 or more units, to have recycling programs.</p>\n	<p class="Default">\n		The determination of whether a business meets the four cubic yard threshold is based upon the level of service to which the business subscribes. <span style="color: #003300;"><b>You can find out if your business falls under this legislation by reviewing your bills to see your can size, or by calling your waste hauler.</b></span></p>\n	<p class="Default">\n		The proposed regulation does not specify how much or what type of materials must be recycled by businesses, nor does it limit the types of materials that could be included in a recycling program. <span style="color: #003300;"><b>A commercial waste generator should comply by either 1) subscribing to a recycling service that includes collection, 2) self-haul the recyclable materials, 3) and/or subscribe to a service that includes mixed waste processing that results in diversion comparable to source separation.</b></span> The proposed regulation provides flexibility and does not dictate how a jurisdiction must implement a program, nor specify that a jurisdiction must implement a commercial collection program.</p>\n	<p class="Default">\n		Local jurisdictions are responsible for education, outreach and monitoring programs that inform businesses of the state requirement to recycle and how they can recycle in their jurisdiction. However, local jurisdictions and waste haulers (or other third-parties) will likely work together and maximize current outreach programs that are already in place. <span style="color: #003300;"><b>Look for information about changes to your waste collection service today.</b></span></p>\n	<p class="Default">\n		<span style="color: #003300;"><b>It is important to note that neither the State nor local jurisdictions are required to take enforcement action on businesses that do not comply with the requirements.</b></span> Each jurisdiction shall report the progress of implementing a commercial recycling program to CalRecycle. This progress shall be reviewed as part of the department''s review in August 2014.</p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-3" style="color: #008000;"><strong>Summary of Presentation</strong></span></p>\n	<p>\n		This presentation provides further information to SSV Members on the new Mandatory Commercial Recycling Law in California. We discuss how your business will be affected and the benefits of the new legislation to your own sustainability initiatives. Questions answered include the who, what, why, when, and how’s of mandatory commercial recycling.&nbsp; The enforcement, compliance, and next steps for your business operations will also be addressed. Lastly, SSV Members <a href="http://www.greenwaste.com" target="_blank">GreenWaste Recovery</a>&nbsp;and <a href="http://www.sswr.com/" target="_blank">Specialty Solid Waste and Recycling</a>&nbsp;are highlighted in how their services are expanding to help provide solutions to their customers. <a href="http://api.ning.com:80/files/LNcVVBK4WiWYY-88gQThwkaDQ-*4P8hhrIr-0DHsRTKIQDAZaNwvx5XX0YUQLc3xkAYe4ENBFI5cgwxTpK0QPeaRX5qY00Sw/MandatoryCommercialRecyclingSSVPresentation.pdf" target="_self">[Presentation]</a></p>\n	<p>\n		<span class="font-size-3" style="color: #008000;"><strong>Introduction to the Fact Sheet</strong></span></p>\n	<p>\n		Sustainable Silicon Valley has provided a fact sheet for AB 341, the new law regarding Mandatory Commercial Recycling. Provided in this sheet are the important facts and dates regarding compliance for your business. We outline new requirements for government and their responsibility for enforcement. Important next steps for your business as well as useful links are also provided to answer specific questions related to your local jurisdiction. <span style="color: #3366ff;"><strong><a href="http://api.ning.com:80/files/dJg*WTOvNd1hCRnbnPodxp4YTrScIrNW7qk2YwS7a6fA*YXWI4HN8AzqombXlocAAMCOjuY87ZiO0E096Yv18SN5yvTRDJq6/MandatoryCommercialRecyclingfactsheetssv.pdf" target="_self">[Mandatory Commercial Recycling - Fact Sheet]</a>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default'),
