	</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n	<strong>Entries will be submitted online and will be reviewed by:</strong></p>\n<table border="0" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="5" style="width: 500px;">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width: 200px; height: 180px;">\n				<a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/ecocloud/index.php/solution_review/expert_profiles"><img alt="Panel of Experts" class="pyro-image alignment-none" src="{{ url:site }}files/large/77" style="width: 250px; height: 190px;" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt="Crowd Sourcing" class="pyro-image alignment-none" src="{{ url:site }}files/large/78" style="width: 250px; height: 190px;" /></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Solutions should:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Exhibit clarity of solution design, be game-changing, implementable and scalable</li>\n	<li>\n		Be a part of an integrated strategy dealing with key social, economic, environmental, policy and cultural issues</li>\n	<li>\n		Be bold, visionary and tangible, focusing on a well-defined need of critical importance</li>\n	<li>\n		Be regionally specific yet globally applicable, and backed up by a solid plan and the capability to move the solution forward</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default'),
(1530, 'default', 43, '<div id="child_page_list" style="margin-bottom: 10px">\n	<ul style="padding: 0px;">\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/showcase-of-solutions-for-planetary-sustainability/about-showcase-of-solutions">About</a></li>\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/showcase-of-solutions-for-planetary-sustainability/entry-criteria">Entry Criteria</a></li>\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/showcase-of-solutions-for-planetary-sustainability/how-to-enter">How To Enter</a></li>\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/showcase-of-solutions-for-planetary-sustainability/review-process" style="color:black">Review Process</a></li>\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/showcase-of-solutions-for-planetary-sustainability/finalists">Finalists</a></li>\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/solutions/workspace">My Solutions</a></li>\n		<li>\n			<a href="/ecocloud/index.php/solution_review/expert_profiles">View Expert Profiles</a></li>\n	</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="span7">\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		<img alt="review_process" class="pyro-image alignment-none" src="{{ url:site }}files/large/80" /></div>\n	<div>\n		<h4>\n			Review Process Overview</h4>\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				The judging of solutions will occur after the submission deadline (January 31, 2013), and will be completed by the end of February 2013.</li>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/ecocloud/index.php/solution_review/expert_profiles">Every submitted solution will be judged by experts from academic, research, business and venture communities, including experienced professors, engineers, entrepreneurs, angel and venture investors, environmental experts and other professionals.</a></li>\n			<li>\n				Solutions will also be reviewed by members of the public through a crowd-sourcing approach.</li>\n		</ul>\n		<p>\n			&nbsp;</p>\n		<p>\n			The submissions will be judged in the following focus areas:</p>\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Resources</li>\n			<li>\n				Human Systems</li>\n			<li>\n				Enterprise</li>\n			<li>\n				Regional</li>\n			<li>\n				Industry</li>\n			<li>\n				Earth Systems</li>\n		</ul>\n		<p>\n			&nbsp;</p>\n	</div>\n	<p>\n		Within these focus areas each solution will be judged for meeting the following&nbsp; solution requirements:</p>\n	<div class="well well-large">\n		<p>\n			<strong>Ratings in each category will range from 0-5</strong></p>\n		<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n			0 - indicating inability to meet the basic criteria</p>\n		<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n			1-2 - promising solution, could use more evidence</p>\n		<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n			3-4 - strong solution with good potential for breakthrough impact</p>\n		<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n			5 - outstanding solution with high potential for breakthrough impact</p>\n	</div>\n	<ol>\n		<li>\n			Creativity - Original Technology, Innovative Application</li>\n	</ol>\n	<p>\n		Assessing the extent to which the work introduces a new or significantly improved solution/technology in an affordable, replicable and sustainable manner</p>\n	<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n		&nbsp;</p>\n	<ol>\n		<li value="2">\n			Approach - Problem Identification, Problem Analysis, Plan for Success</li>\n	</ol>\n	<p>\n		Assessing how well solutions are able to identify the problem being addressed, and how well solutions are analyzed. Additionally, assessing the short, medium and long term plan for implementation and plan to measure success of the solution</p>\n	<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n		&nbsp;</p>\n	<ol>\n		<li value="3">\n			Goals - Game Changing\n			<ol style="list-style-type:lower-alpha;">\n				<li>\n					Multiple Categories (solution integrates a number of elements)</li>\n				<li>\n					Mitigation Strategy (solution helps reduce future global warming or pollution)</li>\n				<li>\n					Adaptation Strategy (solution helps humanity adapt to affects of global warming already in progress)</li>\n				<li>\n					Scalable (solution can be widely adopted so that impact will be significant)</li>\n				<li>\n					Reasonable Risk, Feasibility (solution is feasible to implement, may require legislation or investment or political will)</li>\n				<li>\n					Ecosystem of Solutions (solutions bring together elements that re-enforce one another, creating an ecosystem of solutions that generate a positive impact in a regenerative manner)</li>\n			</ol>\n		</li>\n	</ol>\n	<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\n		&nbsp;</p>\n	<p>\n		Solution descriptions should include plans for assessing achievement of these goals.</p>\n	<p>\n		&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class="pull-right">\n	<div class="widget text_box">\n		<div class="contents">\n			<p>\n				&nbsp;</p>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				<a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/ecocloud/index.php/solutions/create" target="_self">Click Here to ENTER A Solution&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </a></p>\n			<p>\n				&nbsp;</p>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				<a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/ecocloud/index.php/solutions/workspace" target="_self">Click Here to VIEW Your Solutions</a></p>\n			<p>\n				&nbsp;</p>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				&nbsp;</p>\n			<h4 style="text-align: center;">\n				<strong>Call for Solutions<br />\n				Competition</strong></h4>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				<img alt="showcase logo" class="pyro-image alignment-none" src="{{ url:site }}files/large/82" /></p>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				&nbsp;</p>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				&nbsp;</p>\n			<p style="text-align: center;">\n				&nbsp;</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default'),
(1577, 'default', 128, '<p>\n	Are you on a Green Team or do you want to start one?&nbsp; You are not alone.&nbsp; Here is a collection of resources to give you ideas and encouragement, get you started, and help you succeed:</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>How to Get a Green Team Started:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/corporate-green-teams-new-social-trend.pdf">Corporate Green Teams: A New Social Trend at Work?</a>: A conference report by AltaTerra Research on what are green teams, how they work, why they are good for a company and lessons learned.</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www1.gadnr.org/sustain/toolkit/index.html">The Sustainable Office Toolkit</a>: Georgia’s Department of Natural resources provides a comprehensive set of guidelines to help offices of all types and sizes create an environmental program.</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www.fs.fed.us/sustainableoperations/green-teams.shtml">Green Team Toolkit:</a> USDA Forest Service provides a variety of tools and hand-out for ideas and ways to start a green team.</li>\n	<li>\n		<u>Green Teams: Engaging Employees in Sustainability: </u>Deborah Fleischer from Green Impact provides a guide on 10 best practices for bringing all employees on board with a company’s sustainability projects.</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/sustainable-value-creation.pdf">Sustainable Value Creation</a>: An excerpt article from Peter Senge''s Book "The Necessary Revolution" discusses sustainability drivers for businesses. The book also covers on how to start a green team. A review on this section can be found <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/how-start-green-team-your-organization.pdf">here</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Green Team Action Tips:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<u>Top 10 Tips to Green Your Workplace:</u> Justine Burt provides multiple green project ideas that can yield a one year or better return on investment at your workplace.</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www.energystar.gov/index.cfm?fuseaction=bygtw.showSplash">Bring your Green to Work</a>: EPA Energy Star offers multiple tips on saving energy in your office</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www.greenbiz.com/news/2008/06/07/corporate-green-teams-sustainable-business-bottom">Corporate Green Teams: Sustainable Business from the Bottom Up</a>: This article explores the activities of three teams from different industries and of different sizes. :</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="http://www.greenbiz.com/news/2008/10/12/leading-middle-power-green-champion">Leading from the Middle: The Power of Green Champions</a>: A high level perspective on how to engage Green Champions and how to keep them motivated.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Presentations: How Other Companies Did It </strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		BJG, Inc.: <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/architecture-green-teams.pdf">The Architecture of Green Teams</a></li>\n	<li>\n		eBay: <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/launching-green-team.pdf">Launching A Green Team</a> and <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/ebay-green-team.pdf">eBay Green Team</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Genentech: <u>Green Genes</u></li>\n	<li>\n		Symantec: <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/facilities-and-greenteams.pdf">Facilities and Green Teams - Working Together</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Syntony Quest: <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/creating-evolutionary-learning-communities.pdf">What makes a Green Team Thrive? Creating Evolutionary Learning Communities</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Intuit: <a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/intuitgreenofficeguide.pdf">How to "Green" Your Intuit Office</a>Survey from SSV Green Team Leaders Meeting:<u> Top Challenges faced by Bay Area Green Team Leaders</u></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<strong>Green Teams in the Bay Area, Community Level:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Burlingame: <a href="https://sites.google.com/site/burlingamecec/">Citizens Environmental Council Burlingame</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Cupertino: <a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/SimpleLiving-SFSouthBayPen/">South Bay/Peninsula Simplicity Circle</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Los Altos: <a href="http://www.greentownlosaltos.org/">Los Altos Green Ribbon Citizens Committee</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Menlo Park: <a href="http://www.menlogreen.typepad.com/">Menlo Park Green Ribbon Citizens Committee</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Mountain View:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://www.greenmountainview.org/">Green Mountain View</a></li>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://mtnviewcsp.ning.com/">Mountain View Coalition for Sustainable Planning</a></li>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://www.coolcities.us/cityProfiles.php?city=132&amp;amp;state=CA">Mountain View Cool Cities</a></li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		Palo Alto:Redwood City: <a href="http://www.sustainablerc.com/">Sustainable Redwood City</a>\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://pa-ceap.pbwiki.com/">Community Environmental Action Partnership</a></li>\n			<li>\n				<a href="http://www.acterra.org/">Acterra: Action for a Sustainable Earth</a></li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		San Jose: <a href="http://www.coolcities.us/cityProfiles.php?city=171&amp;amp;state=CA">San Jose Cool Cities Team</a></li>\n	<li>\n		Sunnyvale: <a href="http://sunnyvalecool.org/">Sunnyvale Cool Cities</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<strong>Existing Green Teams at Schools:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Palo Alto Unified School District: <a href="https://sites.google.com/site/gunnenvironmentalclub/gunngreenteam">Gunn Green Team</a> and <u><a href="http://www.sustainablesv.org/sites/default/files/dms/gunn-high-school-green-team.pdf">Gunn Green Team SSV Presentation</a></u></li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, ''),
(1579, 'default', 145, '<p align="center">\n	<span style="font-size:18px;"><strong>Microsoft</strong> <strong>Sustainability</strong> <strong>Review<br />\n	November</strong> <strong>2012</strong></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;">Introduction</span></h2>\n<p>\n	Microsoft Corporation is an American multinational corporation headquartered in Redmond, Washington that develops, manufactures, licenses and supports a wide range of products and services related to computing. Bill Gates and Paul Allen founded the company on April 4, 1975. It has around 94,000 employees today.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Awards,</strong> <strong>frameworks</strong> <strong>and</strong> <strong>accomplishments</strong> <strong>as</strong> <strong>of</strong> <strong>Nov.</strong> <strong>2012</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>Awards</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		2012: Microsoft was honored for its investment in sustainable power by the US Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		2012: Microsoft India received the Environment Management Award at The Green IT Initiative and IT Excellence Awards</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>Rankings</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		2012: #3 in the list of organizations using the larger amount of green power by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		2012: #17 in Greenpeace''s Guide to Greener Electronics for their policies on toxic chemicals, recycling and climate change&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		2012: #47 in NEWSWEEK Global Green Ranking</li>\n	<li>\n		2012: #12 in NEWSWEEK U.S. Green Ranking</li>\n	<li>\n		2012: Third largest user of green power according to EPA’s Green Power Partnership ranking</li>\n	<li>\n		2012: Second for green power use for the first-time ranking of tech companies by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>Frameworks</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Global Reporting Impact: citizenship report, G3, undeclared (since 2007)</li>\n	<li>\n		United Nations Global Compact (since 2006)</li>\n	<li>\n		Carbon Disclosure Project:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				2012 global 500: Carbon Performance Score B</li>\n			<li>\n				2012 S&amp;P 500 USA: Carbon Disclosure Score 99 (highest score)</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		2009: Microsoft topped Goldman Sach’s GS Sustain Framework for the global software and services sector. The GS SUSTAIN framework seeks to “identify companies best-positioned to sustain competitive advantage and superior returns through analysis of 1) return on capital, 2) industry positioning, and 3) management quality with respect to environmental, social &amp; governance (ESG) issues”</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>Listings/Index</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		World Dow Jones Sustainability Index (2012, 2010, 2009)&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		USA Dow Jones Sustainability Index (2012, 2010, 2009)</li>\n	<li>\n		<a href="https://indexes.nasdaqomx.com/data.aspx?IndexSymbol=QCRD&amp;menuIndex=0">NASDAQ OMX CRD Global Sustainability 50 Index</a> (2010)</li>\n	<li>\n		FTSE KLD Global Sustainability Index (2012, 2011, 2010, 2009, 2008, 2007)</li>\n	<li>\n		Calvert Social Index (2012, 2011, 2010, 2009)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Sustainable</strong> <strong>Actions/Initiatives</strong></span></p>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">Biodiversity/Site</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:12px;">Microsoft’s Real Estate &amp; Facilities organization led an evaluation of smart building applications from three vendors across 13 buildings on its main campus. This program consisted in adding an analytical layer on top of existing building management systems and did not change existing infrastructure. The program first addressed energy efficiency through:</span>\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				<span style="font-size:12px;">​</span>“Fault detection and diagnosis INSERT INTO `page_chunks` (`id`, `slug`, `page_id`, `body`, `parsed`, `type`, `sort`, `class`) VALUES
(1583, 'default', 140, '<div>\n	<p>\n		<strong><span style="font-size:18px;">Application of LEED rating program for Energy Efficiency</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n	<strong>By Jyothsna Giridhar</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">The ‘idea’ of energy efficiency gained popularity during the energy crisis of 1970s. A lot of studies were undertaken on existing energy conserving technologies and research &nbsp;was carried out on viable energy efficient strategies and alternatives for production and consumption of energy. An average of 30% of the energy produced in United States is consumed by building operations and maintenance (USGBC, 2009). Efforts to make buildings more energy efficient gained more patronization from the 1990s with the development of various green building rating systems, starting with the BREEAM rating system, followed by HQE and LEED.</span></p>\n<p>\n	LEED is one of the preferred rating systems in the US. LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) is a voluntary consensus based rating system developed by the USGBC. The first version of LEED was launched in 1998. It aims to evaluate building performance based on five categories: Sustainable Sites, Water Efficiency, Energy and Atmosphere, Materials and Resources and Indoor Environmental Quality, wherein, it aims to simultaneously address resource conservation and healthy built environment. Within LEED there are various rating systems to address the requirements of various building typologies. The various rating systems are listed below:</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LEED NC (New Construction): Facilities where the owner is the primary occupant.</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LEED CS (Core and Shell): Facilities where the tenant is the primary occupant.</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LEED for Homes</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LEED for Schools</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LEED Neighborhood Development</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LEED CI (Commercial Interiors): Tenant spaces in multi tenant office buildings.</p>\n<p>\n	·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LEED EB (Existing Buildings) addresses the requirements of buildings one year or older and which seeks to gain a LEED rating.</p>\n<p>\n	This article focuses on how LEED addresses energy efficiency for new and existing buildings.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Energy efficiency and LEED</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	Reducing building energy use has a direct impact on running costs of the building, resources spent on energy production and CO2 emissions into the atmosphere. Building orientation, massing, envelope, design of building services, operation and maintenance, usage pattern of occupants, amongst other factors, have a great impact on building energy performance.</p>\n<p>\n	The LEED rating system assesses energy performance of facilities based broadly on the following criteria.</p>\n<h4>\n	Commissioning and retro-commissioning of building systems</h4>\n<p>\n	This requirement seeks to ensure that the installation, calibration and performance of building systems are as per the project team’s requirements and satisfies the design intent. Systems to be commissioned includes HVAC systems, lighting and daylighting systems, domestic hot water systems, renewable energy systems installed within the site, at the minimum.</p>\n<p>\n	For retrofitting projects commissioning would address space temperature, space pressurization, building envelopes (caulking, sealing), primary HVAC systems, AHUs, control systems, lighting systems including all fixtures and their controls, and water systems.</p>\n<h4>\n	Building Performance</h4>\n<p>\n	Building performance improvement for new buildings is demonstrated through simulation comparison to ASHRAE baseline as spelt out in Appendix G of ASHRAE 90.1 2007. Alternatively buildings less than 20000 sqft are required to comply with ASHRAE Advanced Energy Design Guide, and buildings 20,000 to 100,000 Sqft are required to comply with Advanced Buildings Core Performance Guide.</p>\n<p>\n	Existing buildings demonstrate performance improvement through energy star rating. A minimum rating of 60 is compulsory. The energy Star Portfolio Manager Tool could be utilized for this.</p>\n<h4>\n	Buildings Operations and Maintenance</h4>\n<p>\n	Operations and maintenance of building systems impact energy performance of the facility in a big way. Existing buildings can take measures to monitor and maintain systems. Additionally educating the operations &amp; maintenance staff on the building systems and their maintenance is recommended.</p>\n<h4>\n	Performance Measurement</h4>\n<p>\n	Performance measurement in terms of emission reduction and running cost comparison of the retrofitted building to pre-retrofitting period is given weightage under LEED for Existing Buildings.</p>\n<p>\n	Other measures include:</p>\n<p>\n	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Elimination of CFCs and HCFCs in the facility: While it is mandatory under LEED to eliminate CFC usage, HCFC usage elimination in the facility is preferred.</p>\n<p>\n	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Installation of onsite renewable energy source</p>\n<p>\n	3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Investment on offsite renewable energy source to offset the facility’s annual energy consumption (New Build).</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:16px;">LEED Credits</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>The following table shows the various LEED credits under the Energy and Atmosphere section of LEED NC.</strong></p>\n<table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td rowspan="2" style="width:133px;height:10px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>Credit</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td rowspan="2" style="width:363px;height:10px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>Title</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td colspan="2" style="width:109px;height:10px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>Points</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width:52px;height:10px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>NC</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:57px;height:10px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>CS</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width:133px;height:15px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>EA Prerequisite 1</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:363px;height:15px;">\n				<p>\n					Fundamental Commissioning of Building Energy Systems</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:52px;height:15px;">\n				<p>\n					-</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:57px;height:15px;">\n				<p>\n					-</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width:133px;height:20px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>EA Prerequisite 2</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:363px;height:20px;">\n				<p>\n					Minimum Energy Performance</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:52px;height:20px;">\n				<p>\n					-</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:57px;height:20px;">\n				<p>\n					-</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width:133px;height:19px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>EA Prerequisite 3</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:363px;height:19px;">\n				<p>\n					Fundamental Refrigerant Management</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:52px;height:19px;">\n				<p>\n					-</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:57px;height:19px;">\n				<p>\n					-</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width:133px;height:18px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>EA Credit 1</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:363px;height:18px;">\n				<p>\n					Optimize Energy Performance</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:52px;height:18px;">\n				<p>\n					1-19</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:57px;height:18px;">\n				<p>\n					1-21</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="width:133px;height:19px;">\n				<p>\n					<strong>EA Credit 2</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="width:363px;height:19px;">\n				<p>\n					Onsite Renewable Energy</p>\n			</td>\n			<td style="wi