(1701, 'default', 71, '<img alt="earthday2012page.jpg" class="pyro-image alignment-right" src="{{ url:site }}files/thumb/68/0" style="float: right; margin: 10px; " />\n<p>\n	<strong>Earth Day Ideas to Challenge and Inspire : </strong></p>\n<p>\n	<b>Idea #1 Audit and Act:&nbsp; Understand and Reduce Your Energy and Water Use</b></p>\n<p>\n	Energy Use:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">National Geographic invites you to The <a href="http://environment.nationalgeographic.com/environment/energy/great-energy-challenge/">Great Energy Challenge</a> which is a National Geographic initiative to help you understand our current energy situation. Explore the GEC to figure out and trim your carbon footprint.</span></p>\n<p>\n	Water Use:</p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Free audits and water-saving device giveaways are available to customers through San Jose Water’s <a href="http://www.sjwater.com/conservation/audit.jsp">Water Audit Program</a> and&nbsp;Santa Clara Valley Water District’s <a href="http://www.save20gallons.org/">Save20Gallons</a> challenge. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />\n	<br />\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #2 Tap Water Campaign</b><br />\n	Challenge yourself and others to give up using bottled water:&nbsp; Fun facts and solutions are available from The Story of Stuff creator Annie Leonard:&nbsp;<a href="http://storyofstuff.org/bottledwater/" target="_blank">http://storyofstuff.org/bottledwater/&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;</span><br />\n	<br />\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #3 Reduce Trash</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Who’s the sparest of them all?&nbsp; Maybe some employees or departments will want to start a friendly competition! &nbsp;Need some inspiration?&nbsp; It’s time to rethink everything.&nbsp; Check out the <a href="http://zerowastehome.blogspot.com/p/tips.html">Zero Waste Family</a> &nbsp;or follow the journey of Beth Terry of Oakland, CA who gave up using plastic in 2007 and has been blogging about it ever since, first as “fake plastic fish” and now as <a href="http://myplasticfreelife.com/">My Plastic-Free Life</a>.&nbsp; And don’t forget the ultimate sustainability challenge (which included producing no trash) issued by <a href="http://noimpactproject.org/">No Impact Man</a>.</span><br />\n	<br />\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #4 Take Small Actions</b><br />\n	Everyone can do at least one little thing, right?<b>&nbsp;</b> And just imagine if everyone did!&nbsp; Any group of individuals can create a group on the website <a href="http://www.onemillionactsofgreen.com/index.aspx">One Million Acts of Green</a> and start a competition.&nbsp; There are lists of “Green Acts” to choose from in various categories.&nbsp; <a href="http://acespace.org/dot">Do One Thing</a> offers mini-challenges as well—rack up the “things” and compare!</span><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #5 Eco-Friendly&nbsp;Garden</b><br />\n	Challenge employees to start a garden, or even a planter on a balcony!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Garden or Backyard Habitat&nbsp;<a href="http://www.nwf.org/" target="_blank">www.nwf.org</a>&nbsp;</span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">California&nbsp;Native Plants:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cnps.org/%20and%20http:/www.bayfriendlycoalition.org/%20" target="_blank">http://www.cnps.org/</a></span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">Bay Area&nbsp;Friendly Landscaping:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bayfriendlycoalition.org/%20" target="_blank">http://www.bayfriendlycoalition.org/&nbsp;</a></span><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #7 Buy Less Pledge</b><br />\n	We all have too much stuff.&nbsp; How about an Earth Day compact among employees to <a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/thecompact/">Buy Nothing New for a Year</a> (or month).</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Feeling sad about giving up stuff?&nbsp; <a href="http://www.youtube.com/storyofstuffproject#p/u/22/9GorqroigqM">Why less stuff is good for you</a>&nbsp;</span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">But what about the small electronics we love so?:&nbsp;<a href="http://storyofstuff.org/electronics/" target="_blank">http://storyofstuff.org/electronics/</a></span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">What are you really putting on your body:&nbsp;<a href="http://storyofstuff.org/cosmetics/" target="_blank">http://storyofstuff.org/cosmetics/</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Okay, so no new stuff, but what about all the old stuff?&nbsp; Give away your unwanted stuff or get what you want, for free:&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.freecycle.org/" target="_blank">www.freecycle.org</a>&nbsp; or exchange clothes at:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.swapstyle.com/" target="_blank">http://www.swapstyle.com/</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #8&nbsp; Buy Responsibly</b></span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">The Buy Less Challenge is over and you are ready to buy something with your new enlightened awareness? Vote with your dollars!&nbsp; Challenge yourself to buy local, fair-trade, and organic.&nbsp; Follow your conscience to the mall . . . or the website!&nbsp; Eco-friendly shopping options abound now, but to give you some ideas:</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.greenhome.com/" target="_blank">www.greenhome.com</a>&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.biggreenpurse.com/" target="_blank">www.biggreenpurse.com</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.greenerprinter.com/grp/welcome.do">http://www.greenerprinter.com/grp/welcome.do</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">and, for a massive infusion of green-available-everything ideas, go to a <a href="http://www.greenfestivals.org/">Green Fest</a> near you.</span><br />\n	<br />\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #9 Eco-Friendly Eating</b><br />\n	Eat local, eat less meat, eat no meat, eat all organic—design a challenge to pull people out of their normal habits and into some that will benefit their bodies and the planet.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.meatlessmonday.com/spread-the-movement/">Meatless Monday</a>:&nbsp; Environmental and Health benefits of eating less meat:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This initiative aims to reduce meat consumption by 15% in order to improve personal health and the health of the planet. Maybe it can be implemented at the company cafeteria?</span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">Health Benefits of a Vegetarian Diet by <a href="http://www.pcrm.org/health/veginfo/index.html">Physicians Committee</a></span><br />\n	<span class="font-size-2">Support <a href="http://www.foodroutes.org/">Local Farms</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Find a <a href="http://www.cafarmersmarkets.com/index.cfm">Farmers Market</a> near you&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Package your food responsibly too!&nbsp; <a href="http://lifewithoutplastic.com/">http://lifewithoutplastic.com/</a>, <a href="http://www.laptoplunches.com/">http://www.laptoplunches.com/</a>, <a href="http://www.lunchsense.com/">http://www.lunchsense.com/</a> just for some fun new ideas, but you can also just dig out some of the re-usable plastic or glass containers you already have and load them up!&nbsp; Look into getting your company logo on some quality re-usable containers as prizes for employees who bring lunch for a whole week, or go meatless.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea # 10 Reduce Car Trips</b><br />\n	Encourage employees to join or start a team to reduce car trips.&nbsp; The alternatives are out there, and having company along the way helps!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.511.org/">511.org</a> can help you plan your trip using public transportation in the Bay Area</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.youcanbikethere.com/">Bike to Work</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://2milechallenge.com/">Clif Bar 2 Mile Challenge</a>:&nbsp; Pick a bike-promoting charity and see if your team wins!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.vanpool.com/">Vanpools</a>:&nbsp; Organize a vanpool and let someone else do the driving</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><b>Idea #11 Green Business Certification</b></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Make it official:&nbsp; Get a green business certification for your company:</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2"><a href="http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/" target="_blank">http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gbb.org/" target="_blank">http://www.gbb.org/</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Green Business Certification for small businesses:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sba.gov/content/green-certification-and-ecolabeling" target="_blank">http://www.sba.gov/content/green-certification-and-ecolabeling</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">Sustainability in Multi-Tenant Spaces and other facilities:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.thegbi.org/green-globes/" target="_blank">http://www.thegbi.org/green-globes/</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class="font-size-2">&nbsp;</span></p>\n', '', 'wysiwyg-advanced', 1, 'default');
