(7, 'Goals', 60, 1, 0, '60% of OVERALL score - Average of all 7 categories'),
(8, 'Game Changing', 14.29, 1, 7, 'Does the solution dramatically change how the problem is addressed as well as how dramatic is the impact on social attitudes, economic aspects and sustainability.(Including behavior, regulation/legislation and the rules of the game).'),
(9, 'Mitigation Strategy', 14.29, 1, 7, 'Solution helps reduce future global warming or pollution'),
(10, 'Adaptation Strategies', 14.29, 1, 7, 'Solution helps humanity adapt to effects of global warming already in progress'),
(11, 'Scalable', 14.29, 1, 7, 'Solution can be widely adopted so that the solution can be implemented'),
(12, 'Minimal Risk/Side Effects', 14.29, 1, 7, 'Identification of likely effects and side effects of the solution. (Likelihood of buyers remorse.) The unintended consequences of the solution, and how significant they are. The risks to the project versus to other things outside the project'),
(13, 'Feasibility (Social and political will, financial, technical) ', 14.29, 1, 7, 'How likely is the solution to occur? Solution is feasibly to implement, may require legislation or investment or political will. (Focus inside the project.)'),
(14, 'Ecosystem of Solutions (Possible matches with other solutions)', 14.29, 1, 7, 'Solutions bring together elements that re-enforce one another, creating an ecosystem of solutions that generate a positive impact in a regenerative manner');
