culture, sustainability means the potential for long-term support of people and their lifestyles. This has impact on environmental, economic, and social dimensions, which affect choices, behaviors, and costs.\n\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '27', NULL, 'topics', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/27', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/27'),
(252, 'Recycle Plastic Bags', 'RethinkWaste and South Bay Recycling have announced that various types of plastic bags are now being accepted for recycling at the Shoreway Environmental Center in San Carlos.', NULL, NULL, 'blog', 'blog:post', 'blog:posts', '17', NULL, 'blog/2012/11/recycle-plastic-bags', 'admin/blog/edit/17', 'admin/blog/delete/17'),
(554, 'How To Use The Site', ' \n	Welcome to EcoCloud™! We hope you will enjoy exploring this site and collaborating with other EcoCloud™ members. Before you start, please be sure to read the Terms of Use, and to ensure harmonious relationships with other EcoCloud™ members, take a look at our Behavior Guidelines.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Here are a few of the things you can do with EcoCloud™:\n\n	\n		\n			Learn from the experience of your peers and the research of top University experts.\n		\n			Broaden your horizons by browsing EcoCloud™ articles and case studies to learn about the field of sustainability, including recent scientific developments. Our articles and case studies are most often contributed by your fellow EcoCloud™ members, so if you see something interesting, connect with the author right here on this site!\n	\n	\n		\n			Connect with partners who can advise you and provide needed supplies for your project.\n		\n			View Partners and Vendors, available in each topic area of the site, to see lists of organizations and companies that are major players in local sustainability projects.\n	\n	\n		\n			Contribute your own content and comments to the site.\n		\n			Post an article, engage in a forum discussion, make a blog post, publicize an event, or comment on the content contributed by others. EcoCloud™ is a forum where you can provide thought leadership, let others know about you, get advice, and make connections.\n		\n			See our Contribute Content page for more details on how to contribute articles, blog posts, photos, and videos to the EcoCloud™ site. We strongly encourage you to take advantage of the opportunity to participate as a content contributor.\n	\n\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '31', NULL, 'how-to-use-the-site', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/31', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/31'),
(555, 'Behavior Guidelines', ' \n	EcoCloud™ serves the sustainability community by providing a respectful venue for communication and collaboration. The site should improve communications, foster involvement, and help further sustainability goals in Silicon Valley. The tone of discussion is intended to be professional and helpful. EcoCloud™ provides a venue for sharing news, providing thought leadership, collaborating on projects, and sending inquiries to other members of the community.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	The members of EcoCloud™ are our greatest asset and must be treated with respect. Site members should work together to maintain a high level of value and ensure that participation is rewarding and satisfying for all members. Toward that end, EcoCloud™ members are encouraged to use the following guidelines:\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	\n		Members should follow good etiquette. The Core Rules of Netiquette from the Netiquette site is a good place to learn about generally accepted standards of behavior on the Internet.\n	\n		Members should take one-on-one discussions to a more private venue. If you have a topic that is of interest to just a few list members, please create a new Group on the site or convene a working group outside the site. You may wish to post a message to the site to say that you are taking a discussion offline and if members want to participate they should email you. List members engaged in a private discussion may want to post a summary back to the list, once the discussion is complete.\n	\n		The EcoCloud™ site is not a forum for debate or political discourse. The primary focus should be the topics relevant to sustainability in Silicon Valley.\n	\n		Personal attacks are unacceptable. Be as courteous online as you would be in person.\n	\n		Fill out your member profile with your real name and email address.\n	\n		Never distribute or sell other members'' email addresses or other profile information.\n	\n		Do not post articles, blog posts, forum messages, or any other content from the site elsewhere without permission of the author.\n\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	EcoCloud™ members who disregard these guidelines will be warned, have their content removed, or be temporarily or permanently removed from the site by the site moderators.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	The EcoCloud™ site is run by members of Sustainable Silicon Valley. If you have questions about site policies or are not sure if a post is appropriate, feel free to contact the EcoCloud™ Editor for guidance at ecocloudcontent@sustainablesv.org.\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '32', NULL, 'behavior-guidelines', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/32', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/32'),
(556, 'Terms Of Use', ' \n	All members of this site agree to the terms of use set forth in this page.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	All members are encouraged to use basic courtesy and best practices as described in Behavior Guidelines. Failure to do so can result in remedial action at the discretion of the site moderators, up to and including cancellation of site membership.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Terms of Use\n\n	By using the EcoCloud™ site, you agree to the following terms and conditions:\n\n	\n		We will not be liable to you or to any third party if we discontinue our service to you or if we modify or discontinue this service.\n	\n		You acknowledge and agree that you assume full responsibility for any unlawful, threatening, libelous, obscene, harassing, abusive or offensive material contained in your communications though this service, any infringement of third party intellectual property rights arising from your communications through this service, or any crime facilitated by your communications through this service.\n	\n		You are solely responsible for your communications through this service.\n	\n		Your use of the service is subject to all applicable local, state, national and international laws and regulations.\n	\n		You agree: (a) to comply with US law regarding the transmission of technical data exported from the United States through the service; (b) not to use the service for illegal purposes; (c) not to interfere or disrupt networks connected to the service; and (d) to comply with all regulations, policies and procedures of networks connected to the service.\n	\n		We make use of the Internet to send and receive certain messages; therefore, your conduct is subject to Internet regulations, policies and procedures. You will not use the service for chain letters, junk mail, spamming or any use of distribution lists to any person who has not given specific permission to be included in such a process.\n	\n		You shall not interfere with another participant''s use and enjoyment of the service or another entity''s use and enjoyment of similar services.\n	\n		We may, at our sole discretion, immediately terminate service should your conduct fail to conform with these terms and conditions.\n	\n		You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Sustainable Silicon Valley, their parents, subsidiaries, affiliates, officers and employees, harmless from any claim or demand, including reasonable attorneys'' fees, made by any third party due to or arising out of participant''s use of the service, the violation of these terms and conditions by you, or the infringement by you, or other user of the service using your computer, of any intellectual property or other right of any person or entity.\n	\n		We may terminate the service with or without cause at any time and effective immediately. We shall not be liable to you or any third party for termination of service.\n	\n		Participants agree that any posts made to the site may be used in Sustainable Silicon Valley printed materials.\n\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Join us. Your participation matters and makes a difference.\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '33', NULL, 'terms-of-use', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/33', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/33'),
(557, 'About EcoCloud', ' \n	EcoCloud™ is a project of Sustainable Silicon Valley.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Sustainable Silicon Valley\n	P.O. Box 576\n	Santa Clara, CA 95052-0576\n\n	Local: (650) 318-3638 ext. 100\n\n	Toll Free: 1 (800) 668-0718\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	The primary address for EcoCloud™ correspondence is ecocloud@sustainablesv.org\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	EcoCloud™ shares Sustainable Silicon Valley''s Board of Directors.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	&nbsp;\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '34', NULL, 'about-ecocloud', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/34', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/34'),
(326, 'Survey from SM County Parks', 'San Mateo County Parks is undertaking a strategic planning process to ensure that our vision for our park system remains relevant and sets priorities for the next five years.\n\nAs we look forward to 2018, we would like to hear from you about your experience in our parks and how you would like to use our parks in the future. In addition, we hope that you will take a few minutes to rank your priorities for our parks over the next five years.\nCompleting the survey takes approximately five minutes, and can be found at: https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/SMCParks2018\n&nbsp;\nPlease complete the survey by October 28, 2012.\n&nbsp;', NULL, NULL, 'blog2', 'blog2:post', 'blog2:posts', '10', 27, 'blog2/view/10', 'admin/blog2/edit/10', 'admin/blog2/delete/10'),
