(731, 'About', ' \n	\n		\n			About\n		\n			Entry Criteria\n		\n			How To Enter\n		\n			Review Process\n		\n			Finalists\n		\n			My Solutions\n                \n			View Expert Profiles\n	\n	\n		\n\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	\n		Click Here to ENTER A Solution\n	\n		&nbsp;\n	\n		Click Here to VIEW Your Solutions\n	\n		&nbsp;\n	\n		\n		\n			\n				Planetary Life Support Systems\n			\n				Life on Planet Earth is sustained by a web of interconnected systems.\n			\n				The economy depends on a well-functioning society, providing rule of law, financial systems, infrastructure, education, culture, etc.\n			\n				The society depends on a healthy environment providing clean air and water, productive soil, food, energy and materials for our “stuff”. Water and material inputs are recycled by nature.\n			\n				Energy comes from the sun (even if it is stored as fossil fuels).\n			\n				We seek your solutions to restore balance and health to the economic, social and environmental systems on which our civilization depends.\n		\n	\n\n\n	\n		Call for Solutions Competition Goals:\n	\n		\n			Bring attention to solutions that can have impact; understand their benefits and tradeoffs; create public demand for action; and, market demand for results.\n		\n			Inspire and stimulate ambitious solutions and foster collaboration (as well as competition to market). Stimulate cross-fertilization among new and mature solutions and across industry, system and sector boundaries.\n		\n			Create ecosystems of solutions that enable green technology to take off in a way that has impact on global systems such as climate and ocean vitality.\n		\n			Reward exemplary solutions/technology that embody the vision of creating resiliency and planetary sustainability.\n	\n	\n		&nbsp;\n	\n		Who We Invite:\n	\n		We invite inventors from established businesses, entrepreneurial ventures, research institutions and labs to showcase solutions that can scale to have a positive impact for sustainability at a planetary level.\n	\n		&nbsp;\n	\n		What we are looking for:\n	\n		\n			Solutions, technology, policy, processes or a combination of both, that:\n			\n				\n					Exhibit multiple benefits\n				\n					Have systemic and game-changing impact\n				\n					Address both mitigation and adaptation to climate change\n				\n					Generate more good &amp; drive less bad\n				\n					Are scalable and adaptable to a broad range of conditions\n				\n					Are feasible and using either current or new technology, resources and know-how\n				\n					Can withstand empirical testing\n					&nbsp;\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n	&nbsp;\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '41', NULL, 'showcase-of-solutions-for-planetary-sustainability/about-showcase-of-solutions', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/41', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/41'),
(191, 'Redwood City Needs Park Ambassadors!', 'Park Ambassadors are park lovers who are dedicated to keeping the parks safe, clean, and fun for everyone. Park ambassadors also help to spread the word about Stulsaft Park''s new dogs off-leash pilot program.', NULL, NULL, 'blog', 'blog:post', 'blog:posts', '11', NULL, 'blog/2012/10/redwood-city-needs-park-ambassadors', 'admin/blog/edit/11', 'admin/blog/delete/11'),
(245, 'Cradle-to-Cradle Inspiration', 'Material flow in a cradle-to-cradle economy means that there is no "waste." Outputs from one process become inputs to another, by design. Attendees at the June SSV Materials Management event heard presentations from expert practitioners from the Cradle to Cradle Products Innovation Institute, Adobe, Speciality Solid Waste and US EPA on how Silicon Valley companies and cities are bringing this transformational (and profitable) vision to reality.\n\nBridgett Luther of the Cradle to Cradle Products Innovation Institute gave a very inspiring and hopeful talk and she has kindly provided her PowerPoint slides for all to enjoy, which also describe their new push to get as many products certified as possible and not being harmful to health or planet. Anyone out there working on non-toxic fire retardants?', NULL, NULL, 'blog2', 'blog2:post', 'blog2:posts', '4', 8, 'blog2/view/4', 'admin/blog2/edit/4', 'admin/blog2/delete/4');
