(581, 'Grass Roots / NGOs', ' \n	Grassroots, Online Calculators, &amp; Collaboration Resources.\n\n	by Mary Kean and Carey Chen\n\n	January 2012\n\n	For a more detailed &amp; and up to date review of new metrics, refer to our Water Metrics Report and the tables on EcoCloud Water Metrics\n\n	This section includes resources, organizations, and websites that are geared to improve collaboration, communication among peer groups so that organizations and businesses can implement water and energy frameworks and benchmarking projects. Also included are water and energy calculators primarily aimed at consumers in order to raise awareness amongst and educate consumer''s best practices\n\n	A Single Drop (ASD)\n\n	• Website: http://www.singledrop.org/\n\n	• Description:"ASD is a non-profit organization building the capacity of self-reliant partnerships to plan, implement, and manage community-driven clean water and sanitation solutions through sustainable organizational strategies, WASH education, and appropriate technologies."\n\n	• Target Audience (User):Public authorities (esp. local gov''ts), community planners, subject matter experts with technical know-how of water-related solutions\n\n	• Source: Blue Planet Network\n	• Date: Founded in 2004\n	• Topics:Best Management Practices, social entrepreneurship\n\n	• Strengths:directly engages local communities, emphasis on developing countries\n\n	• Limitations:community-driven, which is highly dependent on organizational capability of each community; requires experts, partners, and staff to build up partnerships to be self-reliant\n\n	• Tags: Best-Management-Practices, social-entrepreneurship\n\n	Calculators: Online Water and CO2 / Energy Calculators\n\n	• Description:Below is a list of websites that include CO2 emissions calculators primarily aimed at consumers; for a more complete analysis of these - see the Excel spreadsheet on EcoCloud. The overall objective is to raise awareness amongst and educate consumer''s best practices.\n\n	• Target Audience (User):consumers, business orgs, communities, government\n\n	• Tags: CO2-calculator, water-energy-calculator\n\n	\n		\n			\n				\n					Name\n			\n			\n				\n					Website\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Carbon Calculators ( list of carbon calculators)\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.co2list.org/files/calculators.htm\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Carbonrally (social media challenges lower carbon use)\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.carbonrally.com\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					CoolClimate\n			\n			\n				\n					coolclimate.berkeley.edu\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					The Infinite Power of Texas Renewable Energy Educational Campaign\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.infinitepower.org/calculators.htm\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Wholly H2O (list and description of calculators)\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.whollyh2o.org/calculators.html\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					SBA Energy Saving Calculators\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.sba.gov/content/energy-saving-calculators-energy-star\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Water Neutral Offset Calculator\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.waterneutral.org/calculator2.asp\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					WECalc (Water-Energy-Climate Calculator)\n			\n			\n				\n					http://wecalc.org/calc/\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Water-Energy Measure Calculator (WEMC)\n			\n			\n				\n					http://doe2.com/download/Water-Energy/WaterSavingMeasures-Calculator-v3.pdf\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Energy Cost Calculator for Electric and Gas Water Heaters\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www1.eere.energy.gov/femp/technologies/eep_waterheaters_calc.html\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					River Network''s water-energy calculators (showerhead, community, toilet, water heating, and new water source impact tool)\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.rivernetwork.org/water-energy-toolkit-understanding-carbon-footprint-your-water\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n	Peer Water Exchange (PWX)\n\n	• Website: http://peerwater.org/\n\n	• Description:PWX acts as a Web-based water sector''s clearinghouse, the global marketplace to select, fund, manage, and track the impact of all water and sanitation projects efficiently, collaboratively, and transparently. "PWX is a platform, process, and human network for funding, soliciting, selecting, managing, and evaluating water projects worldwide. It is a participatory decision-making system to oversee thousands of grassroots water and sanitation projects worldwide efficiently, effectively, and transparently."\n\n	"Today, we partner with 73 members (e.g. implementer, funders, analysts), working in 23 countries. We showcase $25+ million of water and sanitation projects on behalf of our members and have directly funded nearly $1.5 million of projects. "\n\n	• Target Audience (User):Business organizations, NGOs, philanthropists, grassroots project organizers and implementers\n\n	• Source: Blue Planet Network\n	• Date: launched in 2006\n	• Topics:Best Management Practices, social entrepreneurship\n\n	• Strengths:scalable, map-driven, low cost field-level work, transparent\n\n	• Limitations:Web-based application may not be practical for projects in far-flung locations\n\n	• Tags: Best-Management-Practices, social-entrepreneurship\n\n	Free PGE Water and Energy Classes &amp; Resource Center\n\n	• Website: http://www.pge.com/pec/classes/index.jsp\\#classresults For a complete list of current PGE classes offered in energy, water, and solar\n	• Description: PGE offers classes throughout the year in topics of water, energy, green building, HVAC, solar, etc. Course length varies: 1 hr to 5 days. Classes are online or at PGE training centers, primarily in San Francisco Bay Area. Many materials and resources are available online and at the PGE Energy Center librarylocated in San Francisco which can be checked out by any resident in PGE Service area.\n\n	• Target Audience (User):consumers, public authorities, water and energy professionals; Some of the classes are introductory and some are for experienced professionals.\n\n	• Tags: energy-efficiency-classes, water-classes, green-building\n\n	\n		\n			\n				\n					High Performance Residential Hot Water Systems\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.pge.com/mybusiness/edusafety/training/pec/classes/index.jsp?reqType=detail&amp;ID=5204&amp;db=PEC5204.csv&amp;pageTitle=Class%20Details%20and%20Registration&amp;postback=yes\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Smart Grid Fundamentals\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.pge.com/mybusiness/edusafety/training/pec/classes/index.jsp?reqType=detail&amp;ID=5055&amp;db=PEC5055.csv&amp;pageTitle=Class%20Details%20and%20Registration&amp;postback=yes\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					The PG&amp;E Pacific Energy Center: Twenty Years of\n					Educating and Serving Building Professionals\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.pge.com/mybusiness/edusafety/training/pec/classes/index.jsp?reqType=detail&amp;ID=5151&amp;db=PEC5151.csv&amp;pageTitle=Class%20Details%20and%20Registration&amp;postback=yes\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Save Water and Energy in Foodservice\n			\n			\n				\n					http://www.pge.com/mybusiness/edusafety/training/pec/classes/index.jsp?reqType=detail&amp;ID=5291&amp;db=PEC5291.csv&amp;pageTitle=Class%20Details%20and%20Registration&amp;postback=yes\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n	Social Networking &amp; Environmental Causes\n\n	• Description:Below is a list of websites that leverage social networking and the traditional networking effect to bring attention to environmental causes. Also included here are various resources that are involved in water sustainability issues.\n\n	• Target Audience (User):consumers, gov''t, communities, business orgs\n\n	• Tags:environmental-causes\n\n	\n		\n			\n				\n					Name\n			\n			\n				\n					Website\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Care2\n			\n			\n				http://www.care2.com/\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Causes\n			\n			\n				http://www.causes.com/sa\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Center for Regional Sustainability, SDSU\n			\n			\n				http://crs.sdsu.edu/\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Make Me Sustainable\n			\n			\n				makemesustainable.com\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					UNEP/SETAC Life Cycle Initiative\n			\n			\n				http://lcinitiative.unep.fr/default.asp?site=lcinit&amp;page_id=9FDF7FDF-261F-4F0E-A8E3-5FF4E16B33C2\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					Report on Water for Business: Initiatives guiding sustainable water management in the private sector\n			\n			\n				http://www.wbcsd.org/web/water4business.pdf\n		\n		\n			\n				\n					WaterSense label (EPA) product certification system &amp; online registry of products\n			\n			\n				http://www.epa.gov/WaterSense/about_us/what_is_ws.html\n		\n	\n\n\n	Water &amp; Energy Sustainability Collaboration Site by Water Research Foundation (WRF)\n\n	• Website: http://collab.waterrf.org/Workshops/WaterEnergySustainabilitySummit/default.aspx\n\n	• Description:The site aims to enable enhanced collaboration between water, wastewater and energy utilities in California. The site design encourages posting of discussions, case studies, web links or other information that will provide enhanced cross stakeholder collaboration.\n\n	• Target Audience (User):Public authorities, water &amp; energy professionals\n\n	• Source: WRF\n	• Date: last updated in June 2011\n	• Topics:water-energy, water and energy sustainability, energy-water research\n\n	• Strengths:emphasizes cross-stakeholder collaboration\n\n	• Limitations:highly dependent on how much/willing/frequent people in water/energy sustainability contribute to site; limited in geographic scope (CA)\n\n	• Tags: water-energy, water-and-energy-sustainability, energy-water-research\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '84', NULL, 'topics/water/grass-roots-ngos', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/84', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/84'),
