(593, 'SunShares', ' \n	What is SunShares?\n\n\n	Silicon Valley Leadership Group has some good news for making home solar installation understandable and affordable.\n\n	Homeowners want to lower their utility costs and use solar to create clean energy but often are confused by the complexity of the process. Researching options is time-consuming and installing upgrades one home at a time is inefficient for contractors and costly to consumers. Developed by the City of San Jose as part of the Department of Energy''s Solar America Cities initiative, SunShares is a first-of-its-kind solar group-buy model that companies and local governments can replicate for highly attractive terms for employees to put solar power on their homes.\n\n	SunShares makes it easy for your employees to save money, cut energy use, and reduce their carbon footprint. The Program groups consumers and leads them through the process to secure a range of financing options that make going solar and increasing home comfort more affordable than ever. City employees were able to get 40% off the market price for installation costs, and subsequent programs with eminent Bay Area companies have seen discounts of approximately 15-20%. Through SunShares, the Leadership Group is seeking to aggregate member company employees throughout the Bay Area. If you’re looking for a great employee engagement program or a corporate social responsibility initiative, SunShares is both! Contact us at SunShares@svlg.org\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Key Takeaways\n\n	\n		\n			SunShares aggregates the buying power of employee groups, providing access to more affordable solar energy and reducing return on investment time for homeowners\n		\n			Helps employees take advantage of state incentives through the California Solar Initiative, federal tax credits, and the benefits of net energy metering through local utilities\n		\n			Demonstrates strong corporate leadership by enabling employees to generate clean renewable energy for their homes while expanding organizational commitment to employee benefit programs\n	\n\n\n	&nbsp;\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '69', NULL, 'topics/systemic/sunshares', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/69', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/69'),
(966, 'Earth Day Ideas', ' \n\n	Earth Day Ideas to Challenge and Inspire : \n\n	Idea #1 Audit and Act:&nbsp; Understand and Reduce Your Energy and Water Use\n\n	Energy Use:&nbsp;\n\n	National Geographic invites you to The Great Energy Challenge which is a National Geographic initiative to help you understand our current energy situation. Explore the GEC to figure out and trim your carbon footprint.\n\n	Water Use:\n\n	Free audits and water-saving device giveaways are available to customers through San Jose Water’s Water Audit Program and&nbsp;Santa Clara Valley Water District’s Save20Gallons challenge. &nbsp;&nbsp;\n	\n	Idea #2 Tap Water Campaign\n	Challenge yourself and others to give up using bottled water:&nbsp; Fun facts and solutions are available from The Story of Stuff creator Annie Leonard:&nbsp;http://storyofstuff.org/bottledwater/&nbsp;&nbsp;\n	\n	Idea #3 Reduce Trash&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n	Who’s the sparest of them all?&nbsp; Maybe some employees or departments will want to start a friendly competition! &nbsp;Need some inspiration?&nbsp; It’s time to rethink everything.&nbsp; Check out the Zero Waste Family &nbsp;or follow the journey of Beth Terry of Oakland, CA who gave up using plastic in 2007 and has been blogging about it ever since, first as “fake plastic fish” and now as My Plastic-Free Life.&nbsp; And don’t forget the ultimate sustainability challenge (which included producing no trash) issued by No Impact Man.\n	\n	Idea #4 Take Small Actions\n	Everyone can do at least one little thing, right?&nbsp; And just imagine if everyone did!&nbsp; Any group of individuals can create a group on the website One Million Acts of Green and start a competition.&nbsp; There are lists of “Green Acts” to choose from in various categories.&nbsp; Do One Thing offers mini-challenges as well—rack up the “things” and compare!\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Idea #5 Eco-Friendly&nbsp;Garden\n	Challenge employees to start a garden, or even a planter on a balcony!\n\n	Garden or Backyard Habitat&nbsp;www.nwf.org&nbsp;\n	California&nbsp;Native Plants:&nbsp;http://www.cnps.org/\n	Bay Area&nbsp;Friendly Landscaping:&nbsp;http://www.bayfriendlycoalition.org/&nbsp;\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Idea #7 Buy Less Pledge\n	We all have too much stuff.&nbsp; How about an Earth Day compact among employees to Buy Nothing New for a Year (or month).\n\n	Feeling sad about giving up stuff?&nbsp; Why less stuff is good for you&nbsp;\n	But what about the small electronics we love so?:&nbsp;http://storyofstuff.org/electronics/\n	What are you really putting on your body:&nbsp;http://storyofstuff.org/cosmetics/\n\n	Okay, so no new stuff, but what about all the old stuff?&nbsp; Give away your unwanted stuff or get what you want, for free:&nbsp;&nbsp;www.freecycle.org&nbsp; or exchange clothes at:&nbsp;http://www.swapstyle.com/\n\n	Idea #8&nbsp; Buy Responsibly\n	The Buy Less Challenge is over and you are ready to buy something with your new enlightened awareness? Vote with your dollars!&nbsp; Challenge yourself to buy local, fair-trade, and organic.&nbsp; Follow your conscience to the mall . . . or the website!&nbsp; Eco-friendly shopping options abound now, but to give you some ideas:\n\n	www.greenhome.com&nbsp;\n\n	www.biggreenpurse.com\n\n	http://www.greenerprinter.com/grp/welcome.do\n\n	and, for a massive infusion of green-available-everything ideas, go to a Green Fest near you.\n	\n	Idea #9 Eco-Friendly Eating\n	Eat local, eat less meat, eat no meat, eat all organic—design a challenge to pull people out of their normal habits and into some that will benefit their bodies and the planet.&nbsp;\n\n	Meatless Monday:&nbsp; Environmental and Health benefits of eating less meat:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This initiative aims to reduce meat consumption by 15% in order to improve personal health and the health of the planet. Maybe it can be implemented at the company cafeteria?\n	Health Benefits of a Vegetarian Diet by Physicians Committee\n	Support Local Farms\n\n	Find a Farmers Market near you&nbsp;\n\n	Package your food responsibly too!&nbsp; http://lifewithoutplastic.com/, http://www.laptoplunches.com/, http://www.lunchsense.com/ just for some fun new ideas, but you can also just dig out some of the re-usable plastic or glass containers you already have and load them up!&nbsp; Look into getting your company logo on some quality re-usable containers as prizes for employees who bring lunch for a whole week, or go meatless.\n\n	Idea # 10 Reduce Car Trips\n	Encourage employees to join or start a team to reduce car trips.&nbsp; The alternatives are out there, and having company along the way helps!\n\n	511.org can help you plan your trip using public transportation in the Bay Area\n\n	Bike to Work\n\n	Clif Bar 2 Mile Challenge:&nbsp; Pick a bike-promoting charity and see if your team wins!\n\n	Vanpools:&nbsp; Organize a vanpool and let someone else do the driving\n\n	Idea #11 Green Business Certification\n\n	Make it official:&nbsp; Get a green business certification for your company:\n\n	http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/&nbsp;or&nbsp;http://www.gbb.org/\n\n	Green Business Certification for small businesses:&nbsp;http://www.sba.gov/content/green-certification-and-ecolabeling\n\n	Sustainability in Multi-Tenant Spaces and other facilities:&nbsp;http://www.thegbi.org/green-globes/\n\n	&nbsp;\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '71', NULL, 'topics/systemic/activities/earth-day-ideas', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/71', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/71'),
(595, 'University Frameworks', ' \n	University Frameworks for Sustainability\nBy Vinodh Valluri, EcoCloud Sustainability Researcher\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	A University wants to go green . . . what does the administration need to do? Where to start? What information will be collected? There are several major guiding frameworks that have come into being and become popular. The attached grid outlines the frameworks available and gives some idea of what is involved.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	University Frameworks Grid\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '72', NULL, 'topics/systemic/university-frameworks', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/72', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/72');
