(627, 'Akraya', ' \n	&nbsp;\n\n	&nbsp;$ &amp; Sustainability- A Success Story of Marrying the Two Greens\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Akraya, Inc., a Silicon Valley-based professional staffing and consulting firm is the living proof that a choosing corporate sustainability is not only an environmentally responsible but also a frugal decision. We owe much of the success of&nbsp; the company’s extraordinary green efforts to a fateful encounter Akraya CEO, Amar Panchal, had while waiting for his car at a local auto body shop. Amar happened upon a certified green business brochure, and immediately decided to learn more about how to decrease Akraya’s carbon footprint. Already long-interested in sustainability, Amar got his management team on board with his green initiative and thus, the “Green Earth, Green Akraya Program” was born.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	The first step in the program was to become a Bay Area Certified Green Business (BACGB). To achieve this, the Akraya staff learned in-depth about the required processes and how it benefited the environment. Using the BACGB Green Business Standards Checklist as a guide, the Akraya team made a to-do list to bring the business’ operations into compliance with the green business standards. The list addressed areas like resource conservation, recycling and pollution prevention. We introduced new recycling and waste management procedures, cut back on our natural resource consumption, and gave the employee break room a “green remodel”. The new employee break room was equipped with a new water filter machine that replaced plastic water bottles, several recycling containers, environmentally-friendly products and a poster with water conservation tactics. Plastic utensils and paper plates were replaced with permanent cutlery and plates and employees were asked to wash their own dishes.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	There was an adjustment period as employees became accustomed to the new ways of doing things around the office, but Akraya overcame these difficulties by taking the time to explain to staff why they were doing this, and shared data about how energy, water, and paper preservation can help the environment. In this way staff members were involved in the process and that helped them understand the implications instead of just making these things mandatory.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	As part of the resource conservation efforts, light bulbs were replaced with eco-friendly LED-certified bulbs and newly installed cubicle glass panels ensured that we maximize using natural sunlight instead of electricity. To prevent air pollution, we joined the Bay Area Air Quality Management District’s Spare the Air Program and introduced a new commute plan that allowed employees to work from home during rush hours when the air pollution report so advised.&nbsp;\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	The company also incorporated the eco-friendly values into its formal office procedures. In addition to implementing a Green Orientation for new employees and a Green Employee Policy, the company premiered the Green Akrayan of the Quarter, a green competition that takes a playful &amp; fun approach to teach employees about how to incorporate green values into their everyday lives.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	Becoming a Bay Area Certified Green Business in early 2009 and providing employees with a comprehensive eco-friendly education was just the beginning. Akraya reached out to its suppliers and encouraged and educated them about corporate sustainability as well. As a result of these measures, Akraya was commended by the city of Sunnyvale, CA for being a poster child of local small green businesses and going above and beyond the green standards. Acterra.org also awarded Akraya with the Climate Hero of Silicon Valley Award in March 2009.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	The changes made as a result of Akraya’s Green Earth, Green Akraya Program also contributed to the company’s bottom line. By eliminating plastic products like utensils and water bottles, Akraya cut back on plastic waste generation by 70%. Paper consumption decreased by 50% due to double sided printing and reusing previously printed paper as scrap paper as well as eliminating paper towels. Akraya also significantly reduced its office supply orders due to a central office supply station set-up by the printer that replaced individual office supplies on each desk. Since we also changed our office temperature settings to lower during winter and higher during summer and battle temperature changes using eco-friendly ways (like wearing a sweater in the office during winter or closing some of the shades to help keep the office cool during the summer), we were able to reduce our energy consumption as well. Our computers are set to stand-by mode if we leave the desk for longer than 5 minutes and the light is motion controlled; these small tricks also helped lower our electricity bill.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	In 2010, Akraya sought to extend its Green Earth, Green Akraya Program to the local community. Akraya partnered with the Northern California Minority Supplier Development Council and PG&amp;E to become a speaker at PG&amp;E’s Diverse Suppliers Go Green Workshop Series. At these panel discussions, Akraya educated large groups of diversity suppliers about the competitive advantages of going green, how the green certificate program works, and also shared useful tips on how to involve internal staff in the process. Through the increased visibility from these workshops, Akraya developed valuable relationships with diversity suppliers and opened a new platform for mentoring other diversity businesses in the procedures of becoming green, which in turn led to new business opportunities.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	From great press to an impact on the bottom line, Akraya has seen firsthand how many bonus benefits can stem from investing in eco-friendly changes in your office. Akraya leadership hopes to reach beyond its direct circle of influence to continue spreading the importance of green education and the notion that committing to environmental sustainability is quite the worthwhile investment.\n\n	&nbsp;\n\n	&nbsp;\n', NULL, NULL, 'pages', 'pages:page', 'pages:pages', '94', NULL, 'topics/systemic/success-stories/akraya', 'admin/custom_pages/edit/94', 'admin/custom_pages/delete/94');
